text: 14 november 2018. as i review thousands of photos, of myself and others, there are so many with tongues hanging out of mouths. quite a few come as a surprise. some of myself i burst out laughing because i’m like wtf? why is my tongue like that?!? a learned response perhaps? i think when i’m thinking hard, i do that with my tongue. then there are the people around me doing the same thing. then come the memories of gooning, but only memories...please use urban dictionary for the meaning of goon, gooner, gooning, etc. a guest in my home  2 sunday’s ago said this...”you think you know what is going on but you have no idea”. the thing is, he is right. i don’t know. i know i was turned into porn...i’ve seen some of it. i know i was drugged and raped...i’ve seen some of it and relive it weekly in my therapy for ptsd...called brainspotting. but do i know the full extent? no. and i’ve accepted that. but it stops with me. i know the people behind it, and i won’t rest until this travesty has been laid bare.

text:
en los meses post #metoo, pareciera que las cosas empiezan a cambiar para nuestrxs vecinxs al norte. dentro de hollywood, el movimiento está teniendo efectos muy reales en los sets cinematográficos; me refiero específicamente al llamado intimacy coordinator que hbo acaba de instaurar para servir de apoyo a las actrices y actores durante las filmaciones de escenas de sexo. éste coordinador de intimidad se encargará de cuidar a lxs intérpretes en esos momentos en los que están más expuestxs, “dando protección física, social y profesional” (kerr 2018). un gran paso para la industria estadounidense. 
en méxico, aún hay mucho trabajo por hacer para la protección de lxs intérpretes y la regularización de procesos que reduzcan las situaciones de riesgo...
.
les comparto una reflexión sobre la regulación de los desnudos en la industria cinematográfica en méxico, lee más aquí 😌👇
.
https://lasgraciasblog.wixsite.com/lasgracias/single-post/el-desnudo-detras-de-camaras
.
foto de @anniespratt en @unsplash .
#actriz #actuación #cine #mexico #nudityrider #intimacycoordinator #reflexion

text:
|| journey to recovery vol.1 ||
~
~
if you’ve read my posts then your up to date with what is going on or know somewhat of the battles i’m fighting through daily.
~
today has been such a gloomy, rainy day. i’m a sucker for cool air and rain. it speaks to my soul in ways i cant put into words. i’m ocd badly to a point where i want my kids to be creative but hate messes. like “let me help you so it won’t be messy!” however it’s good to let them get messy and create using their imaginations.
however this new me that is starting to evolve, embraces messes. it started raining and i went outside and started jumping in those puddles that i dreaded my kids going in.
~
my old ways was still me but i think the me that has been hidden by fear, pain, trauma, hurt, rejection, betrayal, lost, not good enough, self doubt, self hatred, no hope, rape, wanting to end my life and almost succeeded, is coming out. embracing new adventures. this has been me along but the real me is evolving. living flexible and carefree. having an open mind to everything and anything!
~
friends who are fighting mental illness...it’s okay if all you did today was breathe!! that’s huge! make a promise to me that you will take time for you. take a second to do something that makes your inner soul happy. stand in the rain! jump in puddles. smile because you’re here and i’m glad you are!! ❤️
~
mamas, anyone....if your fighting demons... if your darkness is so dark and you don’t have the strength to fight anymore....message me! i’m here for you!! you have someone here that knows how dark it can be or could get. i’m here to listen. always!
name: E M I L Y  H I C K

~
mamas, anyone....if your fighting demons... if your darkness is so dark and you don’t have the strength to fight anymore....message me! i’m here for you!! you have someone here that knows how dark it can be or could get. i’m here to listen. always!

text:
#mehrrealitätaufinstagram . hmm, ich versuche mich mal an ner liste.
🔸️mir brennt ab und zu mal das essen an, insbesondere wenn ich die linsensuppe im emailletopf aufwärme. das aktuelle malheur ist passiert, als ich gerade dabei war, ein foto für instagram zu machen. 😂
🔸️seit ich so viel auf smartphone oder computertastaturen tippe, ist meine ohnehin nicht so hübsche handschrift exorbitant scheusslich geworden. 🔸️ich bin staturmäßig mehr so hummel als biene, geschweige denn wespe. zugleich tanze ich sehr gerne gesellschaftstanz und rege mich immer extrem auf, wenn ich an tanzpartner gerate, die der auffassung sind, dass stämmige frauen sich nicht bewegen können oder wollen, und über ihre vorurteile dann jegliche form der etikette und höflichkeit vergessen. manchmal verleiden mir solche erlebnisse dann auch den spaß am tanzen allgemein.
🔸️ich bin genervt davon, wieviel in der welt abhängig von vitamin b und selbstmarketing ist, wie wenig substanz manchmal zählt, und finde, für menschen sollte es auch so tolle initiativen geben, wie für hutzeliges, nicht normgerechtes gemüse und obst. sowas wie @culinarymisfits oder
@ruebenretter zu adaptieren wäre doch toll, oder? 🔸️es befremdet mich, wenn menschen meinen, es reiche aus, das facebookprofilfoto in flaggen zu ändern, kritische artikel zu teilen oder ## wie #metoo oder #wirsindmehr zu benutzen. im virtuellen raum stellung zu beziehen ist wichtig, ersetzt aber zivilcourage im echten leben nicht.
🔸️die vielen schlechten und schwarzmalerischen nachrichten in den medien überwältigen mich manchmal, und die tatsache, dass ein reaktionärer nationalismus sich auch in der unmittelbaren nachbarschaft breit macht, beunruhigt mich. ich frage mich, wie es sein kann, dass man nicht aus der geschichte lernt.
🔸️einer meiner grundsätze ist: alles was du sagst sollte wahr sein, aber nicht alles, was wahr ist, musst du auch sagen. so agiere ich auch in sozialen medien. wenn ich hübsche fotos teile, dann nicht um über mängel der realität hinwegzutäuschen, sondern weil ich hübsche fotos mag, und ich außerdem überzeugt bin, dass positive energien positive reaktionen begünstigen. selffulfilling prophecy in schön gewissermaßen.

text: years ago, i entered into a legal battle. it was a coming of age story - a survivor reclaiming her power. when it started, my lawyers advised that i not write anything about it. not even in private. those types of things become evidence, i learned, and sometimes the emotional processing and asking that lands on paper might serve the soul, but makes a mess in legal settings. spoiler alert: the justice system is backwards. so there i was, a lifelong writer who hated my own voice and held a grudge against god for giving me the ability at all. a writer who, despite a stint in journalism and mild success in certain circles, walked away. i was already silent. i had stopped writing years before there was a case to protect. the requirement to put my pen down was the permission i so desperately craved. it was permission to deny myself and turn inward. when the case ended, i felt empowered and heard. i realized that, for far too long and by my own free will, i had thrown away my own words. i operated in a toxic bubble of self-doubt, embarrassment, zero self-worth and crippling shame. my return to my voice, my words, has been life giving. ironically, i don’t have the words for it. i am forever changed. if there is anything that i hope you hear, it’s this: please don’t abandoned your power. ask all of the questions. challenge others to consider new perspectives. speak up for yourself, and for others. don’t allow the bigger, intimidating players of society to convince you that your voice is too small or insignificant to be raised. it’s not. we need you. we need to hear you. don’t fear disagreement. don’t fear judgement. don’t fear your own voice. you have power in your throat. raise hell when you need to and bring forth peace as often as possible. there are people, institutions and rules that will try to silence you along the way. don’t help them. don’t join them. be bold in your statements, be courageous with your truth, be unapologetic in your curiosity. and when the hand of the person next to you isn’t seen, use your power to raise your voice in their direction. and hey, if you’ve been quiet in your life, shame does not live here. i have your back. many of us do. 🖤

text:
trump and his people are awful!!!! ——- the museum of african-american history and culture is in part a catalog of cruelty. amid all the stories of perseverance, tragedy, and unlikely triumph are the artifacts of inhumanity and barbarism: the child-size slave shackles, the bright red robes of the wizards of the ku klux klan, the recordings of civil-rights protesters being brutalized by police. the artifacts that persist in my memory, the way a bright flash does when you close your eyes, are the photographs of lynchings. but it’s not the burned, mutilated bodies that stick with me. it’s the faces of the white men in the crowd. there’s the photo of the lynching of thomas shipp and abram smith in indiana in 1930, in which a white man can be seen grinning at the camera as he tenderly holds the hand of his wife or girlfriend. there’s the undated photo from duluth, minnesota, in which grinning white men stand next to the mutilated, half-naked bodies of two men lashed to a post in the street—one of the white men is straining to get into the picture, his smile cutting from ear to ear. there’s the photo of a crowd of white men huddled behind the smoldering corpse of a man burned to death; one of them is wearing a smart suit, a fedora hat, and a bright smile.
 their names have mostly been lost to time. but these grinning men were someone’s brother, son, husband, father. they were human beings, people who took immense pleasure in the utter cruelty of torturing others to death—and were so proud of doing so that they posed for photographs with their handiwork, jostling to ensure they caught the eye of the lens, so that the world would know they’d been there. their cruelty made them feel good, it made them feel proud, it made them feel happy. and it made them feel closer to one another.

em 2015, eu formei em medicina mas eu não queria sair da faculdade sem deixar minha marca. então eu decidi encontrar um jeito de partilhar meu conhecimento das técnicas de primeiros socorros. no dia 22 de março de 2016 eu dei minha"

text_retweet:
#repost @elisabethsubrin
・・・
alas, #bernardobertolucci, who just passed away. he was celebrated throughout his career as a brilliant director, a “a genius auteur,” a “master.” his films were undeniably original, stunningly visualized and psychologically complex. i admire many of them. but he was also undeniably a male filmmaker of his generation — exploitative of women actors, in particular maria schneider,
an early #metoo survivor and bravely vocal about her exploitation on the set of her first major film, which she said left her feeling “a little raped.” and for which he said he had no regrets. he passed away at the same time as paris’ huge #noustoutes interesectional feminist rally yesterday. i’ve written about last tango in  paris elsewhere, for example on my blog who cares about actresses, which is dedicated to schneider. this is a drawing of schneider and bertolucci - a “towering figure” - in a series of maria studies i did while researching her life - drawn from a film still of them on set in 1972.

text:
harrowing!! sometimes it's so hard to review a movie strictly based on the technicalities and analysing the perfection it is made with. especially, when it deals with a grim subject as this does and it only makes it even more appalling when you learn that it's based on some real life experience which someone had. it's only fitting this story comes out now, in the wake of the #metoo movement, where people are still bickering over the credibility of some of the claims. sometimes, we rely too much on the certitude and evidence of something, rather than evaluating the possibility of the actual truth, by bringing the integrity of the claimant. 
the movie, which is an actual memoir of the director, jennifer fox, tells us about the bitter experience - which she failed to apprehend as one, in a very coherent and unapologetic manner. it tells us how our memories try to conciliate with something which is so frightening and vulnerable in order to keep us going forward, only to leave the scars behind and the wounds wide open. the cast did a perfect job. elizabeth debicki and jason ritter were wonderful at portraying their complex, thankless characters. isabelle nélisse, sister of the talented sophie nélisse, was so impressive along with laura dern and ellen burstyn. this was truly an oscar worthy performance from laura dern, to portray the entanglements of her character while making the audiences feel what "jenny" is going through or what she went through. this movie and the topic it deals with, is something we have to put a lot of thoughts on. 
@thetalemovie @hbo @isabelle_nelisse @jason_ritter @lauradern

text: obituary: days after the death of #celebritymom #kimporter media mogul announced her own mother has died. vernita and #oprah had a longtime rift because @oprah says she was raped and  became #pregnant at age 14. she gave up the baby for #adoption her mother had also given up a child - #oprah sister patricia, who later tracked down her family information and sold her harrowing story to the tabloids. oprah spoke on that saying: “for the first time, i realized that that was a gift to me. pat going to the tabloids and telling the story about my having the baby was a gift because it released me from the shame that my mother still carries today [for giving up pat]. i thought, had she not done that, i would still be exactly where my mother is—stuck in the shame.” addressing her mother during a televised reunion with patricia, winfrey added, “you can let that go. you can let the shame go. there are millions of people all over this country who are just like you, who have given up their children because they knew at the time that they could not provide the best for them. so, vernita, you can let that go.” #blacktwitter #blackmoms #metoo #sexualabuse  source: essence magazine read: https://www.essence.com/amp/celebrity/what-oprah-learned-from-her-mother-quote/

text:
@thelilynews is partnering with @smithsonian’s “long conversation” to share what makes women thinkers optimistic. swipe to see what grassroots advocate mily treviño-sauceda has to say.
•
“the long conversation” is a collection of 30-plus thinkers sharing what makes them hopeful for the future. once a year, scientists, artists, space explorers, drag queens, inventors and others convene in washington, d.c., for an eight-hour relay of mini-convos to discuss what's on the horizon.
•
the “long conversation” will be on friday, dec. 7. stay tuned for a giveaway of two tickets to the session of your choice. the giveaway will be open to residents of the washington, d.c., metro area. #thelongconvo (photo by noe montes; illustration by @thelilynews)

text:
two women, a mother and her daughter, pray at the grave of a family member who was murdered by her boyfriend. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for “femicide,” the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio. 
#opensociety #argentina #niunamenos #femicide #femicidio #conmisderechosnotemetas #16days #genderbasedviolence #metoo #hearmetoo

text:
many evangelicals do not believe women should lead churches or preach to men. since beth moore began teaching a women’s bible study at houston’s first baptist church in the early eighties, she carefully followed the rules and refrained from advising men about their behavior. but in october 2016, after she read about the 'access hollywood' tape of donald trump bragging about sexually assaulting women, she couldn't stay quiet any longer. she spoke up about her own experience of sexual abuse as a child, and accused misogynistic male evangelical leaders of being driven by “sin” and “ungodliness.” by speaking up about women experiencing what she described as “horrific abuses” at the hands of high-ranking christian leaders, moore did something momentous: she ignited the #metoo movement among evangelical women. read more about moore, one of the texans included in our december power issue, at the link in our bio. 🎨: @maxomatic
•
•
•
#bethmoore #tmpower #powerissue #metoo

text:
#untothewhirlwind is here to share love, insight and bring up every concept people ignore, reject and refuse to discuss. #mentalhealth & #wellness 
i share my problems. i determine a habit or a possible solution. 
i try to incorporate new things into my life to enrich the experience.
the very same thing is extended to my #audience.
here, i will never shy away from lifting someone's spirits up!
because, i too know what you mean, or how you feel or felt those same feelings- at one point and time... possibly or maybe not.

ℹto me, there seems to be many emotions many people have never felt before and there are so many we can experience at any moment based off life changing in an instant. 
alls im saying is this ig platform is here to offer #positivity & #optimism to the masses!

text:
if you think you might be experiencing domestic violence, there are things you can do: .
.
.
-	you are not alone. reach out – speak to someone you trust or get in touch with a specialist who can offer you help and support. -	it is not your fault – abuse is a choice your partner makes and only he is responsible. that is how he shows who he is. -	domestic violence is a crime therefore illegal. you can free yourself from violence. contact the police authorities in your area. -	contact 061 681 66 33, stiftung frauenhaus beider basel. .
.
#betterworld #stopviolence #noviolenceagainstwomen #orangetheworld #hearmetoo #metoo #speakupwomen #beleivesurvivors #timesup #aiesec #aiesecbasel #youthspeak #basel #switzerland  #womenempowerment #together #stronger #respect #respectwomen #walktogether #girlpower #women #womensupportingwomen #fiercefemale #girlsrock #youarenotalone #femaleempowerment #femalepositivity #woman #eliminationofviolence

text:
r.i.p .
.
"i left the ending ambiguous, because that is the way life is." .
.
~  bernardo bertolucci

p.s ~ curtains

bernardo bertolucci, who died on monday at the age of 77, has received widespread acclaim for  #filmmaking, winning #oscars, #goldenglobes, and the first-ever honorary palme d’or award at the #cannesfilmfestival in 2011

but one part of his career has been the subject of increasing scrutiny in recent years: a #rape scene in bertolucci’s 1972 film last tango in paris. marlon brando’s character, paul, rapes actress maria schneider’s character, jeanne, using a stick of butter as lubricant. in a 2007 interview with the daily mail, schneider said the scene wasn’t in the original script, and that brando and bertolucci had told her about it just before they began filming.

the scene is intended to be #violent and disturbing with paul hitting jeanne and penetrating her as she cries. but as schneider made clear the feelings of #violation we see onscreen aren’t just acting — they’re real. “i was so angry,” she said. “i felt humiliated and to be honest, i felt a little #raped both by marlon and by bertolucci.” the scene became the target of renewed scrutiny beginning in 2016, when a 2013 video clip in which bertolucci discussed the film went viral. the director acknowledged that he’d sprung the butter detail on schneider at the last minute, because he wanted her onscreen humiliation and rage to be real. “i wanted maria to feel, not to act,” he said.

brando didn’t actually penetrate schneider in the scene. but it was an incident of real sexual humiliation nonetheless, by all accounts. and in a time of reckoning around sexual misconduct, misogyny, and abuse of power in hollywood, it deserves to be remembered as part of his legacy.

bertolucci argued that it was necessary to humiliate schneider in order to make his #film. but that argument reveals a fundamental #inequity that the #metoo movement is only beginning to expose: in #hollywood, some people, most of them men, have the power to decide what makes great #art — and who deserves to get hurt in order to create it.

ref. https://www.vox.com/2018/11/26/18112531/bernardo-bertolucci-maria-schneider-last-tango

text:
the picture on the left is me 12 years ago! then a victim now a victor! .
.
i am one of the few fortunate to be alive. some  left in a body bag and while many still suffer domestic violence because it remains widespread and is often considered "socially acceptable” in nigeria. .
.
this is the reason family, friends and even some religious bodies do not see domestic violence as such a big deal. they believe it’s the outcome of provocation and admonish victims never to annoy their abusers . but these abusers don’t hit their bosses or colleagues who provoke them at work . they exercise restraints! .

domestic violence is not a result of provocation. i’m writing this in capital letters and i hope it sinks in! violence and abuse is a tool used to enforce control, power and fear in a relationship or marriage and not a momentary expression of anger.
.
so stop judging victims by saying they were battered because of an imagined, perceived or rumored wrong or asking them annoying questions like “what did you do that made him beat you”. questions like these are unintelligent and insensitive.
.
violence against women isn't cultural, its criminal. real men don't use violence! we must all join hands to eliminate violence against women and girls. our women must feel and know that they are not alone! .

there is no excuse for violence against women.  and yes, no excuse for violence against men either. 
don't justify it....don't judge them!
.
i am a victim turned victor ready to help other victims. join in , let's make a difference! .
.

text:
اعتراض به نامگذاری فرودگاهی به نام «نرودا»

فعالان حقوق بشر نسبت تصمیم دولت شیلی برای نامگذاری یکی از مهم‌ترین فرودگاه‌های این کشور به نام «پابلو نرودا» شاعر برنده نوبل ادبیات اعتراض کردند.

به گزارش ایسنا به نقل از گاردین، «پابلو نرودا» نویسنده برنده نوبل ابیات بود که با شعرهایش به زندگی و دشواری‌های زندگی مردم معمولی آمریکای لاتین می‌پرداخت و زندگی او به عنوان نمادی از مقاومت در مقابل دیکتاتوری شناخته می‌شود. 
با این وجود تصیمیم اخیر شیلی برای نام نهادن یکی از شلوغ‌ترین فرودگاه‌های این کشور به نام این چهره ادبی با اعتراضات فراوان فعالان حقوق بشر رو به رو شده است چرا که آن‌ها معتقدند این افتخار شایسته کسی نیست که در یکی از آثارش به تجاوز اعتراف کرده است. 
کمیته فرهنگی مجلس سُفلای شیلی این ماه و با رای‌گیری اعلام کرد که قرار است فرودگاه «سانتیاگو» این کشور را به نام «پابلو نرودا» تغییر نام دهد. «کارولینا مارزن» یکی از نمایندگان مجلس شیلی و موافق این طرح گفت نام «نرودا» به عنوان کسی که موجب افتخار و غرور همه شیلیایی‌هاست باید اولین چیزی باشد که بازدیدکنندگان با ورود به کشور آن را می‌بینند. 
در چند وقت اخیر انجام چندین اعتراض دانشجویی علیه «پابلو نوردا»  در شیلی که غالبا توسط تشکل‌های فمینیستی انجام شده، شهرت این نویسنده و شاعر نامدار را به مخاطره انداخته است. «کارن ورگارا سانچز» فعال دانشجویی معتقد است دلیل واضح و روشنی برای تغییر نام فرودگاه وجود ندارد، آن هم در زمانی که زنان با شروع جنبش‌هایی چون #metoo در تلاش هستند تا سوء استفاده‌کنندگان جنسی را محکوم کنند. 
این جنجال‌ها همگی به دلیل صفحه‌ای از کتاب خاطرات «نرودا» است که در آن به تجاوز به زن خدمتکار در سال ۱۹۲۹ اعتراف می‌کند. اگرچه این کتاب خاطرات بیش از ۴۰ سال پیش منتشر شده است اما این بخش از خاطرات در سال‌های اخیر مورد توجه و محل بحث و جنجال شده است. «ایزابل آلنده» نویسنده مطرح شیلیایی و فعال حقوق زنان نیز معتقد است که آثار «نرودا» هنوز ارزشمند هستند اما من نیز مشابه بسیاری طرفداران جوان حقوق زنان در شیلی از برخی از ابعاد زندگی و شخصیت «پابلو نرودا» منزجر هستم اما با این وجود نمی‌توان نوشته‌های او را نادیده گرفت. تعداد کمی از افراد بویژه مردان صاحب قدرت و نفوذ رفتارهای قابل تحسینی دارند و متاسفانه «نرودا» فردی خطاکار بود، همچون همه ما که به نحوی خطا می‌کینم.

کمیته فرهنگی مجلس سُفلای شیلی این ماه و با رای‌گیری اعلام کرد که قرار است فرودگاه «سانتیاگو» این کشور را به نام «پابلو نرودا» تغییر نام دهد. «کارولینا مارزن» یکی از نمایندگان مجلس شیلی و موافق این طرح گفت نام «نرودا» به عنوان کسی که موجب افتخار و غرور همه شیلیایی‌هاست باید اولین چیزی باشد که بازدیدکنندگان با ورود به کشور آن را می‌بینند. 
در چند وقت اخیر انجام چندین اعتراض دانشجویی علیه «پابلو نوردا»  در شیلی که غالبا توسط تشکل‌های فمینیستی انجام شده، شهرت این نویسنده و شاعر نامدار را به مخاطره انداخته است. «کارن ورگارا سانچز» فعال دانشجویی معتقد است دلیل واضح و روشنی برای تغییر نام فرودگاه وجود ندارد، آن هم در زمانی که زنان با شروع جنبش‌هایی چون #metoo در تلاش هستند تا سوء استفاده‌کنندگان جنسی را محکوم کنند. 
این جنجال‌ها همگی به دلیل صفحه‌ای از کتاب خاطرات «نرودا» است که در آن به تجاوز به زن خدمتکار در سال ۱۹۲۹ اعتراف می‌کند. اگرچه این کتاب خاطرات بیش از ۴۰ سال پیش منتشر شده است اما این بخش از خاطرات در سال‌های اخیر مورد توجه و محل بحث و جنجال شده است. «ایزابل آلنده» نویسنده مطرح شیلیایی و فعال حقوق زنان نیز معتقد است که آثار «نرودا» هنوز ارزشمند هستند اما من نیز مشابه بسیاری طرفداران جوان حقوق زنان در شیلی از برخی از ابعاد زندگی و شخصیت «پابلو نرودا» منزجر هستم اما با این وجود نمی‌توان نوشته‌های او را نادیده گرفت. تعداد کمی از افراد بویژه مردان صاحب قدرت و نفوذ رفتارهای قابل تحسینی دارند و متاسفانه «نرودا» فردی خطاکار بود، همچون همه ما که به نحوی خطا می‌کینم.

.

your story is your gift!

text:
25 november is international day for the elimination of violence against women.

1 in 3 women experiences physical or sexual violence in their lifetime, usually from a male partner. this inflicts deep physical and psychological wounds. worst, girls and women are left without recourse or justice, forced to continue living under threat, often side by side with perpetrators enjoying impunity.

we must break the silence and speak out. we must stop seeing women as victims, to empower them as forces of change in their lives and communities. we must start as early as possible, with girls, on the benches of schools.

our position is clear. violence does not just harm women, it weakens societies as a whole. at a time when all countries are seeking new sources of creativity and dynamism, no one can be left behind, no society can afford to discriminate against half of its population, half of its imagination, half of its ingenuity.

the rights and dignity of girls and women are foundations for a better future for all. this is why we must eliminate all violence against women. @unesco

text: mamamen' son unos trajes de corte masculino con portabebés incorporados. 'secret strike lleida' es una acción-manifestación en contra de la violencia de género. con ellos, la artista @aliciaframis ha llevado el #metoo a performance. a través de la moda, el diseño, la arquitectura, el videoarte y el activismo, la exposición 'pabellón de género' que alicia framis ha ideado junto con la comisaria margarita aizpuru, articula una conversación sobre el papel de la mujer en nuestra sociedad. la exposición también cuenta con obras que relacionan objetos y espacio, como 'one night tent', en la que los trajes de una pareja han sido confeccionados con el objetivo de que, al desnudarse, puedan montar una tienda de campaña en la que practicar relaciones sexuales. ‘pabellón de género’ podrá verse en la sala alcalá 31 de madrid del 29 de noviembre de 2018 al 27 de enero de 2019.

'secret strike lleida' es una acción-manifestación en contra de la violencia de género. con ellos, la artista @aliciaframis ha llevado el #metoo a performance. a través de la moda, el diseño, la arquitectura, el videoarte y el activismo, la exposición 'pabellón de género' que alicia framis ha ideado junto con la comisaria margarita aizpuru, articula una conversación sobre el papel de la mujer en nuestra sociedad. la exposición también cuenta con obras que relacio objetos y espacio, como 'one night tent', en la que los trajes de una pareja han sido confeccionados con el objetivo de que, al desnudarse, puedan montar una tienda de campaña en la que practicar relaciones sexuales. ‘pabellón de género’ podrá verse en la sala alcalá 31 de madrid del 29 de noviembre de 2018 al 27 de enero de 2019.

text:
.⁣⁣
my name is gaby @gaby_tsu & i created this page with @izzy.mcdowell ❤️🙌🏻 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
we decided to take part in the 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign (from 25 november, the international day for the elimination of violence against women, to 10 december, human rights day) which is a time to galvanize action to end violence against women and girls around the world.⁣⁣
⁣
⁣
before asking other girls to speak up about their own experiences, i thought i should share my own story. ⁣
⁣
⁣
i was in  toxic relationships as almost all of the men i have been in relationships were violent in many different ways.⁣⁣
⁣
⁣
please remember that violence is not just physical but also psychological harm.⁣⁣
⁣
⁣
according to @whiteribbonaust ⁣⁣
a woman may be experiencing abuse if a man in her life:⁣⁣
⁣
⁣
• unfairly & regularly accuses her of flirting or being unfaithful;
• controls how she spends money⁣⁣;
• decides what she wears or eats⁣⁣;
• umiliate her in front of other people⁣⁣;
• monitors what she is doing, including reading her emails & text messages⁣⁣;
• discourages or prevents her from seeing friends & family⁣⁣;
• threatens to hurt her, the children or pets;
• physically assaults her (hitting, biting, slapping, kicking, pushing);
• yells at her;
• constantly compares her with other people; and/or
• constantly criticises her intelligence, mental health & appearance.
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
————- i will be sharing more of my experiences for the next #16days for #hearmetoo #orangetheworld .⁣⁣
⁣⁣
if you have experienced any abusive relationships or any assaults let’s speak up & tag us / use #empowerourwomentoday 🌈🙏🏻⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
no more silence.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
together we are strong and end violence against women!!!!⁣⁣

text:
have you or someone you love been the victim of #bullying or #abuse ...? i haven’t done a blog entry lately, so i wanted to say a few words about how targeted people can defend themselves from #narcissistic and #sociopath abuse especially during this emotionally volatile time of year ... thank you for all of that people who defended me against my harasser the other day... but don’t cry for me argentina... i didn’t highlight that situation because i want or need sympathy... i highlighted it precisely because i want other victims of #abuse to know that they are not alone and they are definitely not powerless... #shantisaks #shamanism #blog ... on protecting yourself from the slinging arrows of a malignant #narcissist...
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
در سریالهایی مثل بازی تاج و تخت نقش زنان و رنج زنان بعنوان یک موضوع برای جذابیت داستان فیلم و اغلب برای سرگرمی ست اما داستان برای سریال « داستان ندیمه» نوع دیگری ست.
.
در این سریال خشونت علیه زنان بعنوان یک امر اخلاقی و الزامی به تصویر کشیده شده.
در فصل دوم نمای کاملی از خشونت علیه زنان به صورت کتک زدن، شکنجه روانی شدن، تجاوز، دزدیده شدن، برچسب گذاری و... به وضوح دیده میشه. درد زنان در این سریال فراتر از دیدن یک فیلم می‌ره. من هر لحظه خودم رو بعنوان بیننده برای درد کشیدن آماده کردم.
.
مردسالاری در این داستان برخلاف ان چیزی که در این روز ها در فضای اینستاگرام دیدیم؛ یعنی بجای مردان، توسط زنان انجام و محافظت و حمایت میشه. همسران، مادران، عمه ها، روسپی ها همگی به سنت ها و خواسته های مردسالاری در این سریال دامن میزنن. درحالی که ندیمه ها مدام از یکدیگر محافظت میکنند؛ همسران و عمه ها در بهترین حالت به وضعیت ندیمه ها بی تفاوت و در بدترین حالت ظالمانه بی رحم هستند.
.
در جهان این سریال طبقه و البته هزار درجه بیشتر جنسیت تعیین کننده ی وضعیت یک فرد بعنوان یک انسان هست.
.
در نهایت مردسالاری و خشونت علیه زنان  رو فقط از سمت مردان نبینیم، برای نگاه و بینشی بهتر بهتون پیشنهاد میکنم این سریال رو ببینید.
.
پینوشت: اینکه تماما خشونت علیه زنان رو در داستان ها و روایت ها و متن های آموزشی منحصرا از سمت مردان کردید خودش یک نوع خشونت علیه مردان هست. .

در این سریال خشونت علیه زنان بعنوان یک امر اخلاقی و الزامی به تصویر کشیده شده.
در فصل دوم نمای کاملی از خشونت علیه زنان به صورت کتک زدن، شکنجه روانی شدن، تجاوز، دزدیده شدن، برچسب گذاری و... به وضوح دیده میشه. درد زنان در این سریال فراتر از دیدن یک فیلم می‌ره. من هر لحظه خودم رو بعنوان بیننده برای درد کشیدن آماده کردم.
.
مردسالاری در این داستان برخلاف ان چیزی که در این روز ها در فضای اینستاگرام دیدیم؛ یعنی بجای مردان، توسط زنان انجام و محافظت و حمایت میشه. همسران، مادران، عمه ها، روسپی ها همگی به سنت ها و خواسته های مردسالاری در این سریال دامن میزنن. درحالی که ندیمه ها مدام از یکدیگر محافظت میکنند؛ همسران و عمه ها در بهترین حالت به وضعیت ندیمه ها بی تفاوت و در بدترین حالت ظالمانه بی رحم هستند.
.
در جهان این سریال طبقه و البته هزار درجه بیشتر جنسیت تعیین کننده ی وضعیت یک فرد بعنوان یک انسان هست.
.
در نهایت مردسالاری و خشونت علیه زنان  رو فقط از سمت مردان نبینیم، برای نگاه و بینشی بهتر بهتون پیشنهاد میکنم این سریال رو ببینید.
.
پینوشت: اینکه تماما خشونت علیه زنان رو در داستان ها و روایت ها و متن های آموزشی منحصرا از سمت مردان کردید خودش یک نوع خشونت علیه مردان هست. .

#metoo #hearmetoo

text:
those of you who know me know that 6 & 1/2 years ago, i survived not only being raped by two strangers, but also  carrying my first born son from that rape, to full term and through the adoption process. it was the darkest and most difficult time in my life. there were few systems set up to offer how much i needed to heal. from this experience, i learned to actively heal myself, connect with my community, and to help support other women with similar stories-go on. 
my vision is to bring clothed, trauma informed, japanese 5 element shiatsu, thai massage, cupping, guasha, reiki and sound healing directly to the doors of women who need it the most.

since 1 in 3 women suffers from sexual assault,  trauma informed bodywork should be as readily available to women as a lyft ride! of those 1 in 3 women who have survived sexual assault, the majority of them are women of color.

through the recent and widespread #metoo movement, more and more people are coming forward to tell their stories, and we have to support them as they open these wounds and allow themselves to be seen, and work towards healing.

if you believe in my vision to offer trauma informed massage to women who need it most please donate and share today! 
i will be eternally grateful!
how you can help: click on the link below and;
1. donate today- every bit helps and it would mean i could answer this calling in my life for women who need it most!✨
2.donate today and share my campaign! sharing with your friends that you have helped inspires them to jump on board too!🌟
3. like and share my campaign with your friends! even if you can’t donate $10 maybe you have 10 friends who can! please consider helping spread the word in this way.🙏🏽 thank you so much!

pre_proc_tweet:
my emotions cannot be expressed in words today. 25th november, international day of elimination of violence against women and i stand with my head up high saying we are rising. 
when i shared my story earlier this year, i thought it was just me. but then it went viral doing that, so many women have come forward too and i am proud to say that we are now a team & a sisterhood. i want the  movement to spread into all communities.

women’s stories of abuse are hidden behind closed doors. we’re here to tell women that you can speak out, and there are people who will see and believe you.

i’d like to take this oppounity to thank the superstar behind the scenes  of  who went above and beyond to suppo this movement.

 for suppoing us on the day and showing us that together we stand united against gender based violence. 
and my amazing team without which this day wouldn’t have been possible
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
to watch the fun video, check out youtube. 
devaw2018

        nothestop

den 25 november är den internationella dagen mot mäns våld mot kvinnor.
varje år dödas minst tretton kvinnor i sverige av en partner och det är ett gigantiskt misslyckande i ett jämställt land. vi måste kalla det vid dess rätta ord: kvinnohat. ・・・
vi behöver nyansera debatten om jämställdhet. frustrationen, frustrationen över att kvinnor, som på ett fredligt och demokratiskt sätt, kämpar för lika möjligheter blir kallade manshatare. när samtidigt #metoo visade på tusentals och åter tusentals av sexuella trakasserier av män på arbetsplatser, på uteställen, på gymmen, i rättssalarna, på gatorna, ja överallt och ingen nämner ordet kvinnohat eller säger att män vill utplåna kvinnor från den här planeten. när det i sverige mördas en kvinna var 3:e vecka av sin partner, och ingen nämner kvinnohat. när ca 7 000 våldtäkter anmäls i sverige varje år, och ingen nämner kvinnohat. medan, om jag skulle få 1kr för varje gång orden manshat eller manshatare använts så skulle jag banne mig bli rik. debatten är så skev. ist för att ha konstruktiva samtal om hur vi får våldet att upphöra, hur vi får lika möjligheter för män och kvinnor behöver vi ”förklara oss” och förklara att vi inte hatar män eller vill eliminera män från denna jord. ist för en rörelse av män för män där fokus är att minska mäns våld mot kvinnor och män (eftersom män står för mer än 83% av allt våld) startas ist rörelser av män för män där det skanderas ”låt män vara män”. obs! det finns fantastiska initiativ också, men de är väldigt få. vi behöver fler och större! hur ska vi göra för att få män att vilja engagera sig för ett samhälle fritt från våld? hur ska vi få män att sluta säga ”inte alla män, jag känner mig orättvist behandlad” till ”jag ser att män som grupp är problemet, jag vill göra skillnad” ?! hur ska man kommunicera för att få till konstruktiva samtal?! hur får vi en debatt som baseras på fakta och där män tar ansvar och agerar aktivt och proaktivt?! jag vill genuint förstå detta, för  om vi får till detta tror jag att vi får till förändring - på riktigt! #kvinnohat #manligaförebilder #jämställdhet
name: Terese Torenfält

text:
💜 support comes in many forms, and sometimes it can be hard to know how or what you can do to help someone or something, especially when we are all 'so busy'.
.
everyone has something they can offer or give away; be it money, gifts, time, labour, love. but i believe the best thing you can do for someone is just show up.. show up completely. if that's the one gift you can give someone, the gift of your space and time, then you have already given that person more than you could ever squeeze into a christmas stocking or wrap up in a box. christmas is about giving and sharing, not about spending money, going to the best parties, or getting the hottest handbag or outfit.
.
here at wrl we are actively giving away the gift of our time, not only this christmas, but from every day forward since i started on this journey. yes i love to donate gifts for causes and events where i can, but my my most treasured asset will always be the gift & exchange of being present 🙇‍♀️
.
i'd like to thank these ladies for all of their support lately. they have proven to me what i have been feeling: you can't measure love by what people give you or don't give you. love is always present, because love is in the heart, the eyes, the soul, the hands... love is in us all. it's all about connection, showing up, being honest enough to be vulnerable enough to show people the real you. wow. thank you ladies for the beautiful gift of support, friendship, sisterhood, acceptance, humility, integrity and positivity. i am rich! ☀️
.
wandering river leila pictured here supporting:
.
➰beach house bling/white ribbon day: wrl donated a brand new handbag and a toiletry bag full of sanitary items to support women who are affected by domestic violence, in connection with beach house bling, redcliffe. @beachhousebling
@shuvaninco
@ranitherese
.
➰kira/beyond blue: we donated 2x custom cutlery kits & a box of chocolates for a fundraiser to raise money & awareness for @kayyb1 's mission of body positivity and mental health, in conjunction with miss diamond australia and beyond blue.
@miss_diamond_australia @beyondblueofficial
@kira.lorinda
.
.
.

text:
8 things i do, despite being told not to:
.
1. discuss religion & politics at supper.
2. watch narcos mexico (weak, netflix).
3. wear my production clothes and help set up before every event. 
4. swerve the car to save an animal.
5. refuse to politely fake-laugh at #metoo jokes & how "difficult it is for men to even banter now". awle poor lads.
6. immediately delete emails that state "revert back asap".
7. look at everyone with an (un)healthy dose of skepticism. minus dogs & ellies.
8. never eat/dress/stand/sit/look/speak/laugh "like a girl".
.
.
.
.
thank you @influentialwomenoftheworld for the mention. fun & funny to be awarded for being anything but.

special announcement! ❤️
we are honored to announce, jennifer boolorn as the first speaker for our 2019, her soul story speaker series! she is the creator, designer and the lead soul behind soul carrier, a handbag company that creates the perfect bag for your unique journey through life.
❤️
jennifer's soul story began when her mother posed the question, "where do you want to go?" just seconds before her life was taken. this pivotal moment in jennifer's life would lead her on a journey to create soul carrier.
❤️
throughout jennifer's presentation you will be asked to think about the question, "where do you want to go?" she will explain what your true north is and how you can become aligned with your true north in everything you do.
❤️
her soul story speaker series presents: jennifer boonlorn
"where do you want to go?" the importance of listening to your soul and aligning all choices with what is your true north.
friday, january 11, 2019

speaker + workshop: 7:00pm-8:30pm

text:
this photo might just be a candid mirror selfie, but there is so much behind this photo that means the world to me. yesterday was the day where during hot yoga i finally took my top off and wore my sports bra, without worrying about the consequences. i even left the room without it on and being able to walk down the stairs at the gym owning my body for the first time in months where i haven’t felt his control felt amazing. this is the first time i’ve gotten changed in the gym changing rooms without worrying about if women can see his scratch marks he left on my boobs after that time i didn’t wear a bra and he tried to pull my nipples off. i didn’t realise how much control he had of me. the clothes i wear to work are chosen by me and only me, what i wear to the beach and to the gym is my choice😁

i may be a person that seems very confident in her skin, at times i’m full of confidence. but the gym is a completely different space for me, it was his place. he knew people looked at what was his and he didn’t like that. being able to get changed in a gym bathroom that’s open plan is huge for me. taking a shirt off in hot yoga is huge for me. being able to be comfortable in my own skin without thinking that he’s going to criticise me is huge for me. life is so precious 🌿and it’s so important to learn, that no man can ever tell you what you can or can’t do, wear or act. if he’s telling you that you can’t ever go braless, show off too much of your legs, wear things that show too much skin. run for the hills. if he’s telling you what to wear, how to act, who you can or cannot hang out with or talk to, it is a sign of emotional abuse. and that is not okay! 💪🏽#metoo #offmychest #hearmetoo #takealoadoff

text:
hola!! hoy les traigo una pequeña review de 'las yeguas desbocadas' de guadalupe loaeza, la cual es la segunda parte de una novela histórica con una mirada femenina muy fuerte.  es la historia de sofía, una chica de clase alta en la joven sociedad de la ciudad de méxico en los años 50. en esta clase alta, las chicas aspiraban a casarse y a adquirir tantos bienes como fuera posible. su círculo social es cerrado y elitista y sus conversaciones giran en cuanto a poder y status. podría ser una novela hartante pero el humor ácido de la protagonista lo hace muy llevadero. sofía esta consciente de sus privilegios y al mismo tiempo esta harta de la sociedad consumista que la rodea, de lo aburrido que puede ser conocer a las mismas personas toda tu vida y vivir las mismas experiencias siempre, no importa que tan lujosas sean estas. un protagonista importante es la ciudad de méxico, los cambios que fue teniendo a lo largo del tiempo, las colonias que antes eran de ricos y que después se  fueron desprestigiado y es interesante ver como seguimos siendo esa sociedad con muchos pobres y pocos ricos, clasista y desesperada por alcanzar el modelo americano. el rol de la mujer es un tema central puesto que estas 'yeguas finas' son las mujeres que se casan por intereses económicos, que son de adorno para sus esposos, que se dedican  a comprar ropa y muebles e ir al club, pero que siguen teniendo aspiraciones, que desean ser algo mas como sofía o por el contrario, como su mamá que desean tener siempre ese lugar de acompañante, pero que siguen siendo seres extremadamente complejos, aun dentro de su mundo de cristal. la primera parte, 'las yeguas finas' me gustó más que esta 2da, pero aun asi es fascinante el microcosmos femenino que construyó loaeza, el cual nos sirve de espejo directo, en cuanto a la función que estamos teniendo individualmente como mujeres en estos tiempos del #metoo y la equidad de género. ¿estamos apoyándonos como  género? ¿o estamos apuñalandonos entre nosotras mismas?

hola!! hoy les traigo una pequeña review de 'las yeguas desbocadas' de guadalupe loaeza, la cual es la segunda parte de una novela histórica con una mirada femenina muy fuerte.  es la historia de sofía, una chica de clase alta en la joven sociedad de la ciudad de méxico en los años 50. en esta clase alta, las chicas aspiraban a casarse y a adquirir tantos bienes como fuera posible. su círculo social es cerrado y elitista y sus conversaciones giran en cuanto a poder y status. podría ser una novela hartante pero el humor ácido de la protagonista lo hace muy llevadero. sofía esta consciente de sus privilegios y al mismo tiempo esta harta de la sociedad consumista que la rodea, de lo aburrido que puede ser conocer a las mismas personas toda tu vida y vivir las mismas experiencias siempre, no importa que tan lujosas sean estas. un protagonista importante es la ciudad de méxico, los cambios que fue teniendo a lo largo del tiempo, las colonias que antes eran de ricos y que después se  fueron desprestigiado y es interesante ver como seguimos siendo esa sociedad con muchos pobres y pocos ricos, clasista y desesperada por alcanzar el modelo americano. el rol de la mujer es un tema central puesto que estas 'yeguas finas' son las mujeres que se casan por intereses económicos, que son de adorno para sus esposos, que se dedican  a comprar ropa y muebles e ir al club, pero que siguen teniendo aspiraciones, que desean ser algo mas como sofía o por el contrario, como su mamá que desean tener siempre ese lugar de acompañante, pero que siguen siendo seres extremadamente complejos, aun dentro de su mundo de cristal. la primera parte, 'las yeguas finas' me gustó más que esta 2da, pero aun asi es fascite el microcosmos femenino que construyó loaeza, el cual nos sirve de espejo directo, en cuanto a la función que estamos teniendo individualmente como mujeres en estos tiempos del #metoo y la equidad de género. ¿estamos apoyándonos como  género? ¿o estamos apuñalandonos entre nosotras mismas?

text:
tomorrow is #givingtuesday, and we are going to be selling these t-shirts to raise funds so we can reach more people with ptsd!
for every dollar raised we can reach 22 people suffering with ptsd.
this is going to be used to reach more people on facebook and give them free resources to help them through their recovery, things like free books, access to our free facebook group, videos, and just overall support.
it's about building awareness about the resources and tools that people suffering can get for free.
there are so many people out there who don't have anyone, or anything to support them.
and a lot of people don't even know that they even have ptsd so it's to help get in front of them and give them the support and love, and really a place for them to come so they can get the help and guidance they need!
thank you for everything <3 hope you have a great rest of your day!!

text:
had someone tell me today that they hated the title of my book. good! that’s the point of the title. to encourage a strong emotion of hate about such a horrible thing. he hated it because of what happened to me and so few are willing to tell the truth about rape. it was such a compliment and he went on to thank me for being so open and raw. i couldn’t even use the title of my book on facebook and had to use my name on this page instead. rape is such a taboo topic but it needs to be addressed for what it is and not sugar coated! it’s heartbreaking, soul crushing, brutally depriving you of a choice that no one should have taken away. 
big thank you to those of you that have reached out and shared their support🙏🙏 #rape #truth #freedom #metoo #notavictim #mst

text:
tbt to this summer. i walked with the dead. every pun intended. i went as spectator at  the zombie walk in stockholm.

in another way i felt more dead than alive. working harder than ever. long shifts, no rest, no time for myself. get home after double shifts and have even more work at home. no safe place to retreat to for recreation and well deserved rest. more dead than alive.

now, i try to spend more time and effort on myself. rebuilding my inner strength, find safe haven. create. trying to feel a sensation of freedom, choice rather than must. 
today i feel a bit better than i have in a long while. for more reasons than i can explain. but one of the biggest reasons is that nine days ago i underwent a complicated surgery to remove old torture scars. for over 8 years i had them. looking in the mirror,  all i could see was their faces, hear their laugh, and feel that tingling sharp pain where the box cutter separated my skin. the surgery might have left me with another scar, and another type of pain. but that pain will go away. now atleast i can't see their faces anymore. when i look in the mirror, i dont see their faces, i only see myself. and now-for the first time in years, i'm finally going to focus on all the things that make me happy, and allow myself to heal. 
#metoo #heal #walkingdead #goth #gingergoth #gothgirl #alternative #selflove

text:
the birthday started early with a russian home-cooked work of art by the insanely multitalented @sonaliza. am still a mix of tears, emotions and too much food so just suffice to list items for the day: lamb chops and russian tea (basically tea with a splash of whiskey); followed by main course: borscht, sourdough bread, homemade mayonnaise (nothing like the store-bought white goo that looks like well.. *cough*). neatly topped off with a biscotti and cranberry-blueberry mascarpone mousse. the last an entirely homegrown creation of the lovely chef. now, more tears. and bed. followed by death. 
#foodcoma #food #family #meals #birthday

text:
i am standing for #orangetheworld campaign by unwomen. @unwomen 
i believe that child marriage is a form of violence against women and girls.

tulisan ini adalah suara saya dan putri*(rekan saya sebagai korban pernikahan dini), gadis, dan wanita yang pernah mengalami dan atau orang tua yang menginginkan anaknya untuk menikah dini.

tidak sedikit orang tua yang berfikir bahwa pernikahan dini adalah salah satu kunci terbaik untuk menyelamatkan anak dari hal - hal buruk di lingkungannya.
siapa yang bisa menjamin anak lolos dari kekerasan seksual dan pergaulan bebas jika ia telah terikat di suatu pernikahan paksa?

sebuah keputusan yang telah orang tua mereka buat, yang tanpa sadar telah merenggut hak mereka untuk menikmati hidup dengan pilihan mereka sendiri.

baru – baru ini telah terjadi pembunuhan dengan modus kecemburuan di kota samarinda ( samarinda seberang ) yang dilakukan oleh suami putri (17 tahun) seorang gadis korban pernikahan dini diatas tuntutan ego orang tuanya. 
dari tulisan ini, saya berharap ada lebih banyak orang yang berbaris di barisan juang menyuarakan bahwa pernikahan dini bukan penyelesaian atas masalah ekonomi, budaya, kekerabatan dsb.

di indonesia pernikahan dini didominasi oleh anak dengan usia sebelum umur 18 tahun.

lalu berdasarkan hukum yang berlaku, usia berapa seseorang dikatakan sebagai anak?

berdasarkan beberapa ketentuan dalam peraturan perundang – undangan yang ada di indonesia tidak ditemui kesamaan yang pasti hingga usia berapakah seseorang bisa dikatakan sebagai anak. sebagian memberi batasan 21 ( dua puluh satu) tahun, 18 (delapan belas), 17 (tujuh belas). hal ini dirasa mengganjal, pada uu perkawinan yang berlaku di indonesia dinyatakan bahwa usia 19 tahun bagi laki-laki dan 16 tahun bagi perempuan bisa melangsungkan pernikahan disertai dengan syarat pernikahan dibawah 21 tahun harus mempunyai izin orang tua. (keterangan di foto selanjutnya). jika memang pernikahan dini terjadi dibawah umur 18 tahun dan dengan izin orang tua, bisa dikatakan bahwa orang tua telah melakukan violence terhadap anaknya sendiri.

text:
where there is violence and abuse, there is no love. ---
last year, we wrote a book for survivors of violence in #afghanistan and around the world. to this day, it has been downloaded in persian and pashtu nearly 1500 times, more than 80 english copies have been bought to support our work, and hundreds of copies have been distributed in kabul, balkh, sar-e-pul, herat, and most recently, khost provinces. for 16 days of activism against violence against women, we will be sharing some key quotes from the book.

text: yes i know i am wife material, but the last person i was with wasn't husband material, he was just a controlling, narracisstic, sociopathic, pathetic, materialistic material, lying ass always tried to keep someone down but not me my mom built me to love me and not care what others say becaise they talked about jesus and what makes me better then him that they aren't going to talk about u rather you're doing good or bad ppl will talk or try and put u down and out every chance they get and most of those ppl be the one that claim they love u but be your biggest hater and worse downfall. so be careful who you meet and fall in love with marry and have kids with because a lot of ppl aren't worth your time and u will final wake up and realise you wasted so much of that time on a person that wasn't good enough for you in the long run and only fed off of you and damn near sucked the life and everything u worked for out of you until nothing is left. i myself are part of the #metoo #whyididntreport movement. sad in your own relationship stuff like rape can happen to males and females. so be careful whom you give your heart and time to because a lot of people are just there to waste your time and take but never give or contribute, because love cannot be bought with material things or money. real love is like a tree with firm roots u cannot just feed it anything and except it to grow, u must care for it, respect it, nurture it, talk to it, listen to it and most of all love it the right way not the way u feel u want to. #aquarius❤ #iknowimwifeworthy #noteveryonedeserveyour💖 #noteveryonedeserveyour⏲

 🎥

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
barbès rochechouart je me retrouve sur son boulevard. 
écouteurs ajustés.
tracy chapman  chante pour mes tympans. 
j’augmente d’un octave.
direction les quais. 
dans mon champs oculaire deux mâles. juste nous. 
chapman chuchote.
je suis toute ouïe.
pas pour elle mais pour eux. 
l’un m’interpelle, je  reste muette. 
l’autre me bouscule, toujours inerte. 
mais prise au bras, maîtrise du geste, brusquée par l’acte, mon corps raidit. j’oublie la langue, je serre les dents. pitié fais passer cet instant.  le bruit des rails raisonne. 
un peu de mouvement, puis beaucoup...
la foule les a refroidis. 
ils s’écartent, me laissant batarde sur le quai.
j’entre dans le métro, essoufflée sans efforts. 
je vibre de peur mais je ravale mes larmes. 
je refais la scène dans ma tête. encore. encore. 
et sans savoir comment, je me traîne dans mon appartement. 
me voila sous la douche lavant toutes traces de cette journée dans les égouts.
-
- diahara haidara
-
———————————————-#metoo #causeitsstillathing #stop #ifyouknowyouknow #butihopeyoudontknow #diamôgouna

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
🧡16 dagar av aktivism!🧡⠀
.⠀
.⠀
hur kan du hjälpa till? i sexton dagar kommer vi dela med oss av tips på vad du kan göra för att bidra i kampen mot mäns våld mot kvinnor. ✊⠀
.⠀
⠀
i samband med #metoo, #timesup, #niunamenos och andra onlinerörelser talar våldsutsatta mer än någonsin tidigare om sina erfarenheter, och det är dags att lyssna. läs berättelser om/med våldutsatta och aktivister runt om i världen genom att följa #hearmetoo på sociala medier och ta in deras berättelser. genom att lyssna kan du förstå och lära dig att se tecken på din omgivning. 🏵️⠀
.⠀
.⠀
ps. du kan alltid stötta organisationer som dagligen kämpar med frågorna, exempelvis vi på fempowerment! du kan enkelt bli medlem via hemsidan, engagera dig som volontär eller bara ge oss ett bidrag så att vi kan stötta fler! 🧡⠀
.⠀
.⠀
#fempowerment #orangetheworldin16days #hearmetoo #16dagaravaktivism #16daysofactivism
name: Fempowerment | Sweden

many individuals struggle with this question after a sexual assault: “why me?” although it is normal to want to find a reason why the assault happened, a victim might begin to blame themselves. the truth is that the victim is never to blame for a sexual assault.
the period of time called the red zone is now over but that does not mean sexual assault on campus can’t still happen. if you or someone you know experiences or has experienced a sexual assault, call the national sexual assault hotline at 1-800-656-4673

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text: the past day or so a lot of past trauma snuck up on me. i was listening to a podcast which triggered some not so great memories. memories of my world and my life not being mine. memories that i tried long to forget. memories i wanted no part of. memories that questioned my worth as a human. memories of my body not being mine. it’s been years since they occurred. years since the trauma. but it struck me yesterday. what happened to be wasn’t okay or normal. i tend to normalize things. say things that happened to me wasn’t so bad. that it just happened to me - not to others by the same person. what happened to me is in the past. i can’t change it. but i need to heal the wounds (hello therapy!). my anxiety and depression have grown in those years.  i have great people in my life now. ones that i know won’t treat me like that. but that doesn’t make it easily go away either. i am putting in the work.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
#metoo  #metoomovement
.
the shocking truth. 1/6 women,  1/33 men, 1/7 children experience sexual assult in thier lifetime. every 2 miniutes someone is sexually assulted. unfortunatly its one of the only crimes that the victim is guilty untill proven innocent. only 22% felt posituve after talking to the police. a whole 71% felt negativly, abandoned and devastated. the only cause of rape and sexual assault is the perpetrator
.
i have been raped twice and sexually assaulted
.
november 2016 - i had been missing for 5 hours, my parents on the phone to the police. i reported what happened. an investigation that lasted 10 months. the case was taken very seriously. dna tests, cctv, forensic examinations, interviews etc. untill they saw my medical records. that day they came to the conclusion because of my past mental health that i was to blame. that i must of done something that caused it. i put myself in a situation that i asked for it. i was humiliated, devastated, broken. it effects ones inner most sense of self and dignity. hearing someone else say the words that so many victims already believe
.
its taken me alot of time to heal, to feel safe. to overcome flashbacks, terror, mistrust etc. it was not my fault. it never was
.
there is no excuse for rape. it doesnt matter how we are dressed, who we were with, what time of day it is, if we were flirting. we have the right to dress how we want, drink, go out where we want. we have the right to live our lives. it can happen to anyone. passed out, spiked, 'stop, leave me alone, get away, dont', turning away, being underaged means no. its not your fault if you didnt know how to stop them or put up a fight, regardless if they are your boyfriend or girlfriend or know them
.
our bodies belong to us as individuals and no one else
.
being forced against your will is a crime
.
although my case was closed, the devastation from it and he walks free i am glad i reported it. his dna remains in the system. perpetrators shouldn't be protected by our silence
.
this is my message to you. don't suffer in silence. it hard to trust, to talk. there is help out there. you are not to blame. there is life after sexual assault and rape.

text:
vero

ne avevo già parlato mesi fa, ma il post lo avevo archiviato dopo pochi giorni siccome ancora non era chiara la dinamica di come si erano presentate le accuse. dopo tanto tempo, eccomi di nuovo qua per parlarne.

nel febbraio di questo anno sono stati postati dei commenti in modo anonimo sul sito web di un giornalino scolastico, sostenendo che dashner fosse colpevole di molestie sessuali. 
quattro di questi denunciavano molestie da parte di dashner e due aggiunsero di averlo segnalato in un sondaggio sulle molestie. 
un commentatore poi ha affermato di essere stato uno degli accusatori, e ha detto che “lo aveva inventato”.
un altro commentatore ha asserito di essere stato soggetto a “mesi di manipolazioni e adescamenti". in seguito a ciò, michael bourret, agente di dashner, ha affermato che non avrebbe potuto continuare a lavorare con lui. lo scrittore ha poi pubblicato su twitter, qui riporto un piccolo stralcio, ma tra le immagini potete trovare tutte le sue parole.
-
"i didn't honor or fully understand boundaries and power dynamics. i can sincerely say that i have never intentionally hurt another person. but to those affected, i am so deeply sorry. i am taking any and all criticisms and accusations very seriously, and i will seek counseling and guidance to address them."
-

è stato poi il turno del suo editore, che ha affermato che non avrebbe più preso in cura e pubblicati i suoi libri.

text:
ecco, la giornata mondiale contro la violenza sulla donna è passata. per ricordarci che “non è normale che sia normale”, vogliamo presentare per tutta la settimana i video degli incontri di 'donne (non più) anonime – confronto sul femminicidio', un progetto ideato e diretto da daniela trincia per albumarte. un anno di incontri e di confronti in un dibattito articolato e spesso molto emozionante, dove sono intervenute artiste femministe come teresa margolles, tomaso binga, rosa jijón, silvia giambrone e roxy in the box insieme a vari esperti sui temi della violenza sulle donne (avvocate psicologhe/i, volontari dei centri antiviolenza, una criminologa, scrittori ed esperti del linguaggio e del linguaggio del corpo, attrici e attori) come sara allegrucci, andrea bernetti, luisa betti, caterina boccardi, matteo bolognese, teresa dattilo, giuseppe esposito, ursula franco, giacomo grifoni, maria francesca palermo, flavia posabella, clara tosi pamphili, alessandra sannella, cristiana guerra, flavia posabella, stefania salatino, maura misiti, titti carrano, tiziana colamonico mensorio, o curatori impegnati anche in arte politica  come francesca guerisoli e angel moya garcia. il progetto si è avvalso del patrocinio gratuito dell’assessorato alle pari opportunità del municipio ii di roma capitale.
questa still è dal primo video che racconta la sintesi del primo incontro che metteva al centro del dibattito la comunicazione, realizzato il 24 novembre 2016. 
per guardare questo e tutti i video di albumarte, seguiteci sul nostro canale youtube ➡ link in bio.
.

ecco, la giornata mondiale contro la violenza sulla donna è passata. per ricordarci che “non è normale che sia normale”, vogliamo presentare per tutta la settimana i video degli incontri di 'donne (non più) anonime – confronto sul femminicidio', un progetto ideato e diretto da daniela trincia per albumarte. un anno di incontri e di confronti in un dibattito articolato e spesso molto emoziote, dove sono intervenute artiste femministe come teresa margolles, tomaso binga, rosa jijón, silvia giambrone e roxy in the box insieme a vari esperti sui temi della violenza sulle donne (avvocate psicologhe/i, volontari dei centri antiviolenza, una criminologa, scrittori ed esperti del linguaggio e del linguaggio del corpo, attrici e attori) come sara allegrucci, andrea bernetti, luisa betti, caterina boccardi, matteo bolognese, teresa dattilo, giuseppe esposito, ursula franco, giacomo grifoni, maria francesca palermo, flavia posabella, clara tosi pamphili, alessandra sannella, cristiana guerra, flavia posabella, stefania salatino, maura misiti, titti carrano, tiziana colamonico mensorio, o curatori impegnati anche in arte politica  come francesca guerisoli e angel moya garcia. il progetto si è avvalso del patrocinio gratuito dell’assessorato alle pari opportunità del municipio ii di roma capitale.
questa still è dal primo video che racconta la sintesi del primo incontro che metteva al centro del dibattito la comunicazione, realizzato il 24 novembre 2016. 
per guardare questo e tutti i video di albumarte, seguiteci sul nostro canale youtube ➡ link in bio.
.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
la peur d'écouter son cœur. 📍lorsque la peur s'installe, c'est toute notre créativité qui est voilée. elle ne disparaît pas, elle est simplement cachée, enfouie, étouffée, comme si la peur et la créativité étaient les deux faces d'une même pièce. les deux côtés cohabitent et sont toujours présents, mais je ne peux être que d'un seul côté à la fois. si je suis dans la peur, alors c'est elle qui prend le dessus, et qui cache ma créativité. même si celle-ci est présente, j'ai retourné la pièce du coté peur, et je ne peux que porter mon attention sur ce côté. jusqu'à quand allons nous jouer à pile ou face avec nos vies ? 🌱 pendant des années, j'ai vécu ma vie en me raccrochant à mon passé, à mon histoire, à mes blessures et à mes peurs. 
tous ces événements m'ont obligé à les traverser, et à les traverser seul, et m'ont permis de voir que personne ne peut faire ce chemin, mon propre chemin, à ma place. si je ne m'aime pas totalement, qui pourra m'aimer ? sans cette histoire, sans ces expériences, sans cette souffrance et sans ces blessures, je n'aurais jamais changé, je n'aurais jamais découvert que ma vie pouvait être différente. cela ne justifie en aucun cas les mauvaises expériences que nous avons vécues, comme ces agressions physiques et sexuelles que nous témoigne cette courageuse anonyme. mais nous avons le pouvoir d'en faire quelque chose, de nous transformer et de dépasser notre histoire et notre souffrance. je ne dis pas que c'est simple, mais je crois en notre capacité. 💡c'est à partir de nos souffrances que notre véritable créativité peut s'exprimer. créer c'est d'abord et avant tout créer notre vie, et transformer notre vulnérabilité en force. la première étape est peut être de m'accepter complètement, d'accepter qui je suis, avec la confiance de savoir que je peux créer ma vie. oui ça fait peur, mais putain que c'est bon. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
cuando las mujeres nos unimos ocurren cosas maravillosas. somos amor, justicia y memoria.

ayer, junto a #lashijasdehipatia, salimos a las calles, sintiendo en nuestros cuerpos y nuestros corazones a todas aquellas que ya no pueden contar su historia. reivindicando en nuestros gritos y nuestros pasos su existencia, para que ninguna de nosotras repita la pesadilla de vivir con miedo, el dolor del maltrato, la injusticia del feminicidio. 
en medio de todo lo que soy, esta es una de mis causas más grandes y ayer fue muy emotivo y conmovedor ver a tantas hermanas gritando en una sola voz #niunamenos. 
25.11.2018 día internacional por la no violencia contra las mujeres. 
#feminismoes luchar todas juntas como hermanas. ••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••

text: i am posting today, to say that after 1.5 years of trauma, counselling, and staying quiet, i went to ottawa police on saturday and am pressing charges. i have watched a woman in my life completely fall apart after an assault from her past corrupted her psychologically. i will not let that happen to me. i am not proud to say that i was sexually assaulted, but i am proud to tell you, i reported. going to the police seems terrifying and daunting, but it’s the right things to do. if you or someone you know has been assaulted, i urge you to go to the police and report it. we are stronger together. you are not only protecting yourself, but you are protecting women who could be assaulted in the future. #metoo #metoomovement #endrapeculture #orangetheworld #enddomesticviolence #survivor #consent #bbg #strongwomen #reportabuse #hearmetoo #believesurvivors

косичка - это отличная альтернатива обычным бортикам. вот, к примеру, некоторые её преимущества:
✔️воздух свободно циркулирует в кроватке🌬
✔️бортик невысокий, и вы можете наблюдать за малышом, а он за вами👀
✔️это оригинальный и стильный дизайн для детской комнаты👍🏼
✔️если малыш уснул на вашей кровати, то выложенная вокруг него косичка, не даст малышу укатиться и упасть🙅🏻‍♀️
✔️бортик косичка прекрасно держит форму и, когда малыш подрастёт, не будет мяться под его ножками👣
✔️такая косичка в будущем отлично впишется в подростковую кроватку💕

please join #cfawl and @ocbayls for a free cle luncheon on friday, november 30, 2018, at the orange county courthouse in the judicial conference room. the topic of the luncheon is the legal ramifications of #metoo. a distinguished panel of speakers will be led by moderator mary ann morgan, former ocba president and member of the florida bar board of governors.

text:
you dont have to live in the gym or be a gym rat to be healthy & fit!
-
-
i know a few of you out there think i’m all about exercise and live in the gym however i am holistic (mental, emotional, physical, spiritual) nothing is more powerful than made up mind.
-
-
in my workshops and lectures i typically talk about the biggest leverage points being: consistent with functional movement (walking #1 exercise), fine-tuning your nutrition and micro nutrition, proper sleep hygiene and being honest by assessing your stress levels.
-
-
for the past year i’ve been dedicated to building strength in my body, it feels amazing to have strength and integration of upper and lower body with the core. the technology and knowledge i got from the @chekinstitute & @paul.chek helped me to put it together systematically for myself first and help others from a place if applied knowledge.
-
-
for many years i’ve heard of clients, friends and followers share their stories about having serious problems with autoimmune issues from limes disease to ms, crohn’s or lupus. -
-
having gone through it myself and healed at 100%, i can be an example of what is possible. so in the end, my dedication to what i’m creating is based on my own journey to self love and fortunately it’s attached to my mission of disrupting our ideas of what is not possible.🙏

text:
an old picture today, to present  you the new text that i wrote. ✒
-english version-
✒
"after the hit"
last night, i went away by train.
leaving the city for my little country.
the spiders were breathing under the wooden floor.
i took a shower, trying to wipe off the blue traces that, your, big fingers did.
the exploded veins looked like massive oceans on my nude legs.
i closed my eyes to be in a total black.
remembering this furniture drawer falling in a noisy silence, breaking my glasses,  i had to think that it could have been my head under this heavy piece of wood.
i open my eyes, finding my air is back.
the ones  who went to visit my house, knows that my bathroom is full of mirrors.
in one of those, i see the reflection of a woman that i don't reconise.
miss shapen i took 10 kilos, love is heavy.
joséphine sapin

text:
gestern war der internationale tag zur beseitigung von gewalt gegen frauen!
jede vierte frau wird in ihrem leben mindestens einmal opfer von gewalt durch ihren partner.
13% der frauen in deutschland wurden schon opfer von sexueller gewalt.
wir müssen laut werden, wir müssen solche schlimmen tatsachen stoppen. wir können was ändern!!
wenn ihr jemanden kennt, oder ihr selber davon betroffen seid/wart dann sucht hilfe! lasst gewalt keine chance. und wenn ihr denkt, es sei richtig oder „verdient“ sich schlagen oder grob anfassen zu lassen von eurem partner, vater, besten freund oder wem auch immer - es ist in keinster weise richtig!
das problem wird immer größer und größer, jedes jahr gibt es mehr fälle.. es ist wirklich erschreckend. wir mädels sollten uns zusammen tun, sollten uns gegenseitig helfen, uns tipps geben und zusammen halten! wir müssen uns nicht mehr diskriminieren lassen.
ich werde euch nun 2 nummern geben, wo ihr euch melden könnt, wenn ihr betroffen seid oder jemanden kennt, der betroffen ist:
sexueller missbrauch: 0800 22 55 530
hilfe telefon gegen gewalt an frauen: 08000 116 016
und wenn ihr keinen zum reden habt, oder angst habt es einer person zu sagen, die euch nah steht, da sie euch „zu nah“ steht, dann schreibt mir, ich bin für euch da!🖤
•
•

regardless of how a brand frames its “corporate responsibility” policies, the bottom line still stands: all fast-fashion is deeply and wholly dependent upon violent working conditions due to their production needs. sweatshops, economic exploitation, and gender-based abuse of garment workers are not a reformable by-product of fast-fashion; they are a systemic, inevitable, and necessary component central to fast-fashion’s model of production, at almost every level of the supply chain.
