text: so i painted over a painting i had done with someone i dated that assaulted me. as a form of therapy, i thought painting over it would provide closure, or a sense of it, but instead, i just kept painting all these different colors on top of each other with no purpose and no goal. just let me know after layer. those pretty purple colors at the top across, those were some of the first colors i painted over with, and that was easy, it flowed. but everything in the inside is a wreck. none of it correlates, at all. it looks hectic. i'm not sure what to make of what this means. #painting #therapy #art #creative #metoo #sexualassault #stillirise #always #strength #women #findstrengthwithin #staytrue

i don't speak on the flat earth topic much on this page, because it has nothing to do with you getting the ruach and avoiding the lake. however, when i talk to my friends away from the gram, i tell them this is how i view the earth, because this is how the scriptures describe it.

when people say the earth is a globe, they are thinking of a full circled globe, like a basketball.
that isn't the only type of globe there is, you also have the half circle globe, like we see in the snow globe toys.

the snow globe toys have been around for hundred of years, and we call them globes without question, yet when you mention the earth being globe people only think of a circular shape.

according to the bible, the earth is the shape of a snow globe toy, a half circle, flat on the bottom with a firmament dome covering the sides and tops.

we cannot confirm either one definitively with our own hand and eyes, because we are restricted from going to the edges of the earth, as well as restricted from going to the top of the earth. of course many of you will say what about the moon landing. that moon landing is and was bullshit, those liars never traveled to the moon, and they never will.

everything this society gives you are a bunch of lies. truth be told we can't prove flat earth, show glove earth or full globe earth, but we can look at the evidence and claims dealing with all three and do the process of elimination.

if you are a sheep that believes in nasa, space explanation, big bang theory and the rest of that nigga shit, then this will surely zoom over your head. if we had the technology to go to the moon decades ago and our equipment and technology has improved considerably since the 50s and 60s, why can't we go today?

think of how much technology has improved in the last 50 years, what's stopping us today?

what's stopping us today, is people being able to u cover those lies today since we have new technology. the first time many people saw television was during the time of the moon walk, so they could make a fool out of them with the shitty graphics, today they can't fool us.

text:
writing has always been cathartic for me. i remember when i was a little girl, i would write in a journal every night before bed. it helped me process my feelings (even if it was something as trivial as who my crush was or why i was upset with my bff). writing in that journal became a lifesaver for me. it was my one and only private space where i could allow myself to be completely honest with how i felt. .
i remember when i was dating my abuser, he saw my journal and laughed at me. he said something along the lines of “only little girls keep diaries.” i stopped writing after he said that. i found only two journal entries from the time i was dating him, and both were from a time when i felt a sudden shift in our relationship and didn’t know how else to process it. i’m sure those two entries helped keep what little sanity i had left. .
and, of course, after i left my abuser, i started writing out my story on her. writing wasn’t only healing, but it was validating. i remember i would often doubt my story, but i could go back and see what i had written and remember my truth. writing kept me grounded. it kept me from second-guessing myself even when others did.
.
i am so, so incredibly humbled and honored today to say that weareher.net has over 200 stories on it today. over 200 ways for survivors to heal, to empower themselves, and to begin restoring their bodies and minds. writing is incredibly healing, and if you still don’t believe me, maybe this except from the apa will change your mind. 💙💜 #weareher
.
.
.
#heal #empower #restore #writing #journaling #journal #speakyourtruth #youareenough #believesurvivors #empoweringwomen #narcissisticabuse #survivor #metoo

text_retweet:
#repost @zikibay with @get_repost
・・・
today is the #internationaldayfortheeliminationofviolenceagainstwomen.
–
🇰🇿 бүгін әйелдерге қатысты зорлық-зомбылықты жоюдың халықаралық күні.
–
🇷🇺 сегодня #международныйденьборьбызаликвидациюнасилиявотношенииженщин.

на пути присоединения казахстана к ведущим странам мира есть большое препятствие – это насилие против женщин.

казахи очень гордый народ. мы любим гордиться своим родным языком, культурой, историей и суверенным государством. однако часто нашу гордость задевают совсем бессмысленные вещи. почему мы не стыдимся того, что ежедневно женщины подвергаются сексуальному харассменту, т.е. домогательствам? почему мы не препятствуем этому, когда это происходит перед нашими глазами? почему нам не стыдно, что женщин в казахстане каждый день избивают, крадут, насилуют и убивают? почему мы не поддерживаем наших сестёр, когда против них совершаются такие преступления? почему нас не оскорбляет тот факт, что от бытового насилия в казахстане ежегодно погибают около 400-500 женщин?

разрушение семьи, нищета, невежество, экстремизм – корень многих проблем казахстана в плохом отношением общества к женщинам. наша страна никогда не исправится до тех пор, пока мы, как общество, чётко не заявим, что «приставать к женщинам – это преступление», «бить женщин – это преступление», «красть женщин – это преступление», «насиловать женщин – это преступление», «убивать женщин – это преступление».
#orangeurworld #orangetheworld #hearmetoo #endvaw #25november #endviolenceagainstwomen #enddomesticviolence #endgenderbasedviolence #16days #немолчи #немолчиkz #dontkeepsilent #dontkeepsilentkz #нетпримирениюснасильником #нетпримирениюснасильникомkz #нетхарассменту #нетхарассментуkz #сообщапобедимнасилие #янебоюсьсказать #metoo #timesup #heforshe #feminism

text:
alas, #bernardobertolucci, who just passed away. he was celebrated throughout his career as a brilliant director, a “a genius auteur,” a “master.” his films were undeniably original, stunningly visualized and psychologically complex. i admire many of them. but he was also undeniably a male filmmaker of his generation — exploitative of women actors, in particular maria schneider,
an early #metoo survivor and bravely vocal about her exploitation on the set of her first major film, which she said left her feeling “a little raped.” and for which he said he had no regrets. he passed away at the same time as paris’ huge #noustoutes interesectional feminist rally yesterday. i’ve written about last tango in  paris elsewhere, for example on my blog who cares about actresses, which is dedicated to schneider. this is a drawing of schneider and bertolucci - a “towering figure” - in a series of maria studies i did while researching her life - drawn from a film still of them on set in 1972. #mariaschneider #lasttangoinparis #bertolucci #whocaresaboutactresses #awomanapart #awomanapartfilm

text:
sketchbooks are a private peak into a person’s life, so this one in the british library is like a portal into the life of olive wharry a suffragette in prison. she served at least six prison sentences for her protests and was jailed for her fire attack on kew refreshment pavilion in 1913. she recorded her time in holloway prison in this scrapbook. it contains poems, limericks, sketches, newspaper clippings and photographs. the ‘winsonosaurus’ cartoon and text are typical of how olive and her fellow suffragettes used humour to get through the difficult times in prison. i wonder what we would record .... #olivewharry #kindredstudios 
#sketchbooks #winsonosaurus

name: Natalie Cronin Artist
tweet_full:
sketchbooks are a private peak into a person’s life, so this one in the british library is like a portal into the life of olive wharry a suffragette in prison. she served at least six prison sentences for her protests and was jailed for her fire attack on kew refreshment pavilion in 1913. she recorded her time in holloway prison in this scrapbook. it contains poems, limericks, sketches, newspaper clippings and photographs. the ‘winsonosaurus’ cartoon and text are typical of how olive and her fellow suffragettes used humour to get through the difficult times in prison. i wonder what we would record .... #olivewharry #kindredstudios 
#sketchbooks #winsonosaurus

text: quelques fragments et souvenirs d’un projet initié en 2014, qui me tenait à cœur, et qui s’intitulait « la cité des femmes », en lointain clin d’œil à fellini. il s’agissait de témoignages de femmes retranscrits graphiquement à échelle humaine. elles abordaient leurs relations à l’espace public au sens large. ce travail me semble plus que jamais d’actualité en cette périodes de marche contre les violences faites aux femmes à paris, ainsi que de la vague #metoo .  #inkdrawing #contemporaryart #art

text:
رفته بودم مدرسه خواهرزاده هفت سالم که ببرمش خونه.
لباس تنش هم که مثل همیشه یک مانتوی مدرسه آبی با مقنعه پوشیده سفید بود و صورتش هم که اصلا آرایش نداشت،یک بچه ساده و پوشیده.
دستشو گرفتم و با خودم بردمش خونه.
تو راه که داشتیم میرفتیم ماشینی از بغلمون رد شد و دوتا پسربچه کوچولو سرشون رو آوردن بیرون و رو به خواهرزادم گفتن«جوووون».
اون هم پسربچه های کوچولویی که تو این سنشون باید بچگی کنن و تربیت صحیح یاد بگیرن نه اینکه تو این سن تبدیل بشن به کسانی که به یک دختر کوچیک تیکه میندازن اونم یه دختر کوچیک که حتی لباسش هم ساده بود و هیچ چیز به اصطلاح تحریک کننده ای هم نداشت.
بعد اون هم روز دیگری این اتفاق افتاد و یک پسر مدرسه ای کوچیک شروع به تیکه انداختن کرد.
الان بازم کسی هست که بگه اشکال از پوشش دختره؟
بعد اون یاد جمله ای افتادم که روی بنر مدرسشون نوشته بودن«با حجاب زن مسلمان،هم زن مسلمان و هم مرد مسلمان امنیت پیدا میکند.»
حالا یک سوال دارم الان این امنیت بود؟
پسرهای کوچیکی که تو این سن دارن تیکه میندازن،فردا که بزرگ میشن چی میشن؟
اینجا الان کیا مقصرن؟زنانی که بدحجاب بودن یا مردانی که از بچگی اینچنین بار اومدن؟
میگن با حجاب زنان هم زنان و هم مردان امنیت پیدا میکنن درحالی که توجه نمیکنن در جامعه ای که در اون بیماران جنسی آزاد میگردن و پسران در این سن اینطوری بار میان،زن رو در هزاران پارچه هم مخفی کنیم و بپوشونیم نه تنها زنان و مردان بلکه حتی کودکان هم امنیت پیدا نمیکنن.
لطفا برای حل مشکل به علت توجه کنید نه به معلول.
.
نوشته #mahdi_rs64 .
#حجاب #metoo #shetoo #بیماران_جنسی #امنیت

text: quelques fragments et souvenirs d’un projet initié en 2014, qui me tenait à cœur, et qui s’intitulait « la cité des femmes », en lointain clin d’œil à fellini. il s’agissait de témoignages de femmes retranscrits graphiquement à échelle humaine. elles abordaient leurs relations à l’espace public au sens large. ce travail me semble plus que jamais d’actualité en cette périodes de marche contre les violences faites aux femmes à paris, ainsi que de la vague #metoo .  #inkdrawing #contemporaryart #art

text:
i am thrilled to announce the official launching of rise (recovery, insight, & survivor empowerment), a 10-week therapeutic support group for women-identified survivors of sexual trauma.
•
•
over the last year, i have poured my heart & soul into the development of this group to ensure that each 90-minute session is deeply impactful & rooted in the most innovative & effective therapeutic interventions for survivors.
•
•
during rise, members will connect with others who have had similar experiences, engage in healing discussions that explore the impact of trauma, & build neuroscience-based coping skills necessary to thrive in today’s world. upon completion, members will have a customized wellness plan that they may carry into daily life with a newfound sense of strength, control, & resiliency.
•
•
for more information on rise, please visit www.drtruitt.com (link in bio). if you’re interested in scheduling a complimentary 30-minute phone consultation to assess if this is the right group for you, please call us at 626.524.5525 or email us at info@drtruitt.com!

yesterday was the international day to end violence against women. this piece by af3irm la sister iris is a testament to the legacies of women who have been planting the seeds for the world we deserve to live in - a world free of violence, where all of our sisters are free to move, to be heard, to be seen and to feel safe. • “they tried to bury us, but they didn’t know we were seeds.” we will keep growing. we will keep rising up. we will keep sharing our stories. we will keep building towards this world, every day. • 
this day sparks 16 days of activism that will conclude on international human rights day, calling for the full humanity of women around the world.

text:
the other half of the population has been on the receiving end of abuse, neglect and violence in different forms, through various stages of their lives. abuse of women and girls - as a social menace, makes no exception; it is prevalent across different layers of caste, culture and education. crime rates reach a new high every passing day with more and more women feeling unsafe in their immediate environment. 
save the children stands strong with the global voice against gender-based violence! 
we have been on our toes, empowering women across the nation and helping them transform their lives.
for the next 16 days, we will share gripping stories of change, hope and most importantly win against all odds. it’s time to end violence against women and girls.
 together we shall #orangetheworld
 #16daysofactivism #hearmetoo @unwomen @sc_campaigns 
#endviolenceagainstwomen #nochildmarriage #womenpower #metoo

text:
hi all-my name is kaitlin and i am awakening's marketing coordinator! #givingtuesday is coming up and i wanted to share why awakenings is so important to me and how you can help us continue to fight for survivors! my entire life has been impacted by sexual assault, and rather than run away from it, i have made the conscious choice to face it every day. as a result, i have found empowerment in my constant journey of healing and recently, that journey has led me to working at awakenings, a small arts nonprofit dedicated to making visible the work of survivors. my trauma fed off of silence; however, awakenings strives to break that silence for all survivors. this work is difficult and taxing, but this is work that needs to be done; however, the burden should not solely rest on the shoulders of survivors. you can help shoulder that burden by making a small contribution this holiday season. even a simple $10 donation can help us buy supplies for our art therapy workshops. if you have the ability, please donate to awakenings on #givingtuesday by clicking the link in our bio!
.

text_retweet:
i know the word feminism is thrown around indiscriminately. everyone is a feminist these days and ofcourse men cannot be feminists according to most feminists. what a load of bs. this video is a beautiful explanation of what is feminism. i was always one to keep screaming and shouting about gender equality even in my teens and i continue to do so even now. i refused to go to my parents house during my pregnancy or after the birth of my child (as mandated by tradition) with the hope that my husband would be an integral part of twils early months and he was as he continues to be even today. for us to be an equitable family. for our at that time unborn child (be it girl or boy) to see a family where roles were not defined based on gender. we wanted to bring up our child had it been a boy to grow up and respect women as being there equal and if it was a girl, for her to know that she can be anything she wants and gender does not define her roles. it’s the generation of our children who are most likely to change the societal norms that exist today and us as partners have the duty to do so. next time you buy your daughter a barbie and your son a gun, remember that you are pegging them by gender. or even when a kitchen set is bought for your daughter and a car for your son. these are very small and innocent ways in which we thrust gender on our children. for the world to be truly equitable, we need a world without gender. #momlife #parenting #parentingquotes #genderneutral #nonconformist #genderequality #feminism #metoo #womenempowerment #girls #heforshe #genderpaygap #womenleaders #mommyblogger #indianmomblogger #motherhood #kids #moms #dads #life #child #love  #repost @swedense with @get_repost
・・・

text:
we still do not know the true extent of violence against women, as the fear of reprisals, impact of not being believed, and the stigma borne by the survivor—not the perpetrator—have silenced the voices of millions of survivors of violence and masked the true extent of women’s continued horrific experiences.

in the recent past, grassroots activists and survivors, as well as global movements such as “#metoo”, “#timesup”, “#balancetonporc”, “#niunamenos”, “hollaback!” and “#totalshutdown” have converted isolation into global sisterhood. they are making offenders accountable, exposing the prevalence of violence from high office to factory floor. today’s global movements are setting collective demands for accountability and action and calling for the end of impunity, to ensure the human rights of all women and girls.

#orangetheworld  #16daysofactivism
#hearmetoo #endvaw

text:
today marks the continuation of #16daysofactivism for 2018.

from 25th november, the international day for the elimination of violence against women and girls, to 10th december, human rights day, the 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign is a time to galvanize action to end violence against women and girls around the world.

the international campaign originated from the first women's global leadership institute coordinated by the center for women's global leadership in 1991.

in recent years, the voices of survivors and activists, through campaigns such as #metoo, #timesup, #niunamenos, #notonemore, #balancetonporc and more locally #lifeinleggings, among others, have reached a crescendo that cannot be silenced any more.

advocates understand that while the names and contexts may differ across geographic locations, women and girls everywhere are experiencing extensive abuse and their stories need to be brought to light.

this year be will represent some stories we have been aware of over the years through the unite campaign’s global advocacy theme: orange the world: #hearmetoo as a means to bring awareness to what girls face daily.

#endviolence #genderviolence #girls #herstory #heartwork #story #likeagirl #advocacy #awakening #awareness #sdg5 #campaign #barbados #pain #cause #charity #change

text:
"those who have never been in an #abusiverelationship struggle to understand how people remain in one for so long. if somebody was mistreating you, "why did you stick around?" they ask.
.
this is because we are conditioned to believe #abuse is always physical. on tv and in films, we see characters who are obviously evil. they are violent to their partners, shout at them aggressively, or even murder them in a fit of rage. while this does happen, it's not a true representation of the abuse many others experience.
.
unfortunately, for many people, when they try to leave these relationships they are so bonded to their abuser that they return. others don't try to leave at all, and are only freed from the clutches of the abuse when they are discarded.
.
an abusive relationship with a #narcissist or #psychopath tends to follow the same pattern: idealisation, devaluation, and discarding. at some point, the victim will be so broken, the abuser will no longer get any benefit from using them. they may have totally bankrupted them, or destroyed their confidence, or worse, and they move on to their next target.
.
however, once they are gone, the victim - or survivor as thomas calls them at this point - can finally start coming round to the idea they were abused. they can grieve, and finally see the damage that was being done, and realise it wasn't their fault.
.
that's when the healing can really begin, thomas says, and the survivor can realise that they were targeted not because they were weak, but because they had so much to give."
.
full article at: https://uk.businessinsider.com/trauma-bonding-explains-why-people-often-stay-in-abusive-relationships-2017-8
.

text:
#violenceagainstwomen is a crime of near epidemic proportions. one in four women in the uk will experience domestic violence in the course of her lifetime. and while it is a crime that is blind to whose life it affects – rich and poor, young and old – we know that many black, asian and minority ethnic women (bme) across the uk face additional hurdles seeking help and protection. - 40% of #bme women live in poverty. - bme and #refugee women experience higher rates of domestic homicide - are 3 times more likely to commit suicide than other women in the uk. - 50% of bme women victims of violence experience abuse from multiple perpetrators.

#risetogether is about highlighting the incredible work these 5 organisations (#lawrs, #apnahaq, #ashiana, #lawa and #imece women’s centre) already do, and helping the uk public take action to support them during the #16daysofactivism to end #vaw (25 november – 10 december). please click #gofundme link in bio to find out more and donate today. no matter how big or small your donation, it will make a huge difference to the lives of hundreds of women! 
#16days #hearmetoo #metoo #womensrights #genderequality

text:
according to the un, 1 in 3 women and girls experience physical or sexual violence in their lifetime, most frequently by an intimate partner.
•
yesterday was the international day of violence against women. to mark this day, thousands of people across europe and the world protested against one of the most devastating violations of our human rights.
•
 while we have made some advancements towards eradicating violence against women - spain for instance is training more than 600 judges on gender violence and preparing to reform the country’s laws on sex crimes - we still have a long way to go. just yesterday for example, the people who were protesting in istanbul were greeted by tear gas and were prevented from marching by the police.
•
#icdo believes that in order to achieve a world in which everyone has equal opportunities, safety and prosperity we must address violence against women and girls immediately. we encourage you to join us and the 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign organized by the women's global leadership institute and help stop violence against women.💪🏽
•
info from: un.org & washington post
.

.
.

text:
m:chile:2018 “the first day that we talked about stories of gender-based violence and discrimination, we talked about it between men and women and different groups. i thought, how are people going to understand this if they are not talking about these topics with people who are vulnerable?”
•••••
for the 16 days of activism, footage will focus on “women ending conflict” by launching a campaign from our girl-talk-girl program featuring new stories from and produced by young women in the school of psychology at pontificia universidad católica de chile. each young woman is the first person in her family to attend university. gtg provides a safe platform for global young women to share experiences of gender-based violence and to heal. [girl-talk-girl was generously funded by the us embassy in santiago and by donors like you.].

text:
sometimes i wonder if he did it on purpose. if he wanted to make me become like him. soulless. alone. 
they say hurt people hurt people. that’s why i never had a call. or a message. he didn’t hit me. he just left me in the streets alone after being abused because i had to “survive by my own”. he didn’t curse me. he just talked to me whenever he needed something, then going back to the silent treatment for months. he wasn’t really mean to me, he was just “sincere”. i couldn’t really claim nothing. we didn’t have any partnership. we were nothing. because me trying to connect with you is also trying to cut your wings, right? you could have done it but i wasn’t the right person, am i wrong? you could have thought better before entering my life and digging a hole for my integrity. i lost three years of my life. i guess you were feeling ok about that. playing with all their bodies and knowing that i would be there waiting for you. you thought that everything was ok, you did nothing. i don’t deserve a phone call, nothing. i stopped waiting a long time ago. you’ve just wasted my time with all of that manipulation and narcissistic behavior. you made me better. but i will not become like you. never.
📷: @martantares.photo .
.
.
.

text:
i founded rising up adventures because i want to use paddle boarding to help women survivors of trauma.
.
.
.
as a survivor myself, i never stop feeling grateful for ocean air, waves and movement of the board over the water. bringing others out into this incredible world is my life’s mission.
.
.
.
this is my daughter, visiting me for thanksgiving. she grew up paddle boarding every weekend with me, in hawaii, with dolphins, exploring waterfalls...
.
.
.
i’m so grateful to have another paddle weekend with my beautiful daughter for thanksgiving.
.
. 
when you paddle with us, your proceeds benefit the development of local adventure therapy groups for survivors of trauma.
.
.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: on your journey to healing, there are several questions you might need to consider in order to recognize and appreciate your milestones. "what do i need?" is a great start. your needs may be emotional, mental, spiritual, or physical, and there aren't necessarily any wrong answers. some of your needs may be a little harder to achieve than others, but the idea is to identify and work towards them to be the best version of yourself possible. working with a professional counselor who can help you sort through your list is also a good idea. remember, you are a survivor! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text:
me too.
⠀
⠀
⠀
хэштег, который используется в соцсетях для осуждения сексуальных домогательств и насилия, ставший популярным после скандала с харви вайнштейном.
⠀
⠀
популяризировала его голливудская актриса алисса милано (всем любимая фиби из "зачарованных").
дальше акцию поддержали леди гага, америка феррера, риз визерспун, бьёрк, хизер грэм и многие другие всемирно известные женщины не по наслышке знающие, о том, что такое сексуальное насилие.
⠀
⠀
в русскоязычном интернете есть свой собственный тэг #янебоюсьсказать
этот флешмоб захватил сеть, тысячи и тысячи девушек и женщин преодолевая страх и чувство стыда, рассказали о своих историях.
⠀
по примерным оценкам 6 и 10 женщин хотя бы раз в жизни подвергались сексуальному насилию. думаю, домогательства претерпели 9 из 10.
⠀
⠀
благодаря таким акциям как metoo и янебоюсьсказать сухие цифры обрели реальные человеческие лица, обросли фактами и ужасающими деталями.
сами женщины наконец увидели, как много жертв! жертв, которым затыкают рот, которых заставляют стыдиться, выдавливают из жизни, показывают пальцами.
⠀
⠀
а по улицам до сих пор ходят мужчины, которые запросто в компании хвастаются коллективным изнасилованиям. и они не сумасшедшие, они не выглядят, как маньяки, эти мужчины милые, улыбчивые, с приятными голосам. они даже не понимают, что они делают. и я знаю лично таких и мужчин, и пострадавших от них женщин.
⠀
⠀
я просто в очередной раз хочу напомнить: жертва никогда не бывает виновата. в насилии всегда виноват насильник. если девушка сказала "нет", это не значит "может быть".
и если вдруг не дай богиня, с вами такое произойдёт (!) не молчите!
⠀
⠀
аминь.

@regran_ed from @fashquake - 
tears.
because tears are not the sign of weekness.
they're a sign of strength !
tears. 
because sensitivity isn't a sign of being a "pussy",
it's facing your damn fears !
imagine if men were as disgusted with rape as they are with "periods"...
this comes not just as a social message on the eve of "international day for the elimination of violence against women" , but also to uncover the harsh truths that prevail in our society, hiding under the covers of "pride" and "ego"..
if it's about being proud, be proud to give women respect, choice and rights on their own bodies.
violence or rape doesn't justify your pride or ego, it only exposes the miseries hidden in that mind.
#timesup for this misery to continue and it's time to #hearmetoo
stop these brainless, inhuman acts and clear your minds, not my character.
be strong but don't hurt ! be a human and don't force #metoo..

text:
crimes against women have increased by a staggering 800(+)% in india in the last five decades... no nation for women takes a close, hard look at what makes india unsafe for its women – from custodial rapes and honour killings to rapes of minors and trafficking – the author uncovers many unpalatable truths behind what we are familiar with as newspaper headlines only

journalist and author priyanka dubey travels through large swathes of india, over a period of six years, to uncover the accounts of disenfranchised women who are caught in the grip of patriarchy and violence.

text:
mi hijo @wawi00 es un regalo de la vida y una bendición.
es mi  fruto de mi existencia y un premio que me entrega el destino.
como en un espejo, siempre estoy con él  ahí para sus momentos buenos y malos también....
son como pedazos de carne, por los que corre nuestra propia sangre y nuestra esencia, aunque no son nuestros. siempre será mi hijo, mi gato rockanrrolero o mi burrito sabanero.... mi dulce, y visionario tesoro, asertivo, responsable, honesto, cuidadoso y prudente, amable, alegre y con su buen sentido del humor, creativo, sensitivo, digno.....🤔bueno soy su madre, a decir verdad si tiene defectillos pero yo los veo como ....puntitos, solamente feliz hoy y siempre de tu cumpleaños ✨🥇me siento elevada de ser tu mamá... ♾ tenía dieciocho años y mi vida cambió completamente y me dije siempre “el me espera con su sonrisa” y le daré lo mejor de mí y sí creo que hice bien ... cuando tenía ocho años me miró y me dijo mi papá no te trata bien y no quiero ver eso..sencillo!!! y así fué ...esperé 8cho meses, 8cho horas y naciste a las 8cho de la noche y mi alma se contentó de que hubieras sido quién eres... y si pude escribir versos y pintar de colores y ahí supe que eras mi bebé querido y mi vida se llenó de estrellas y sé que estás conmigo. tenemos que valorarnos y darle a nuestros hijos un hogar libre de violencia y maltrato.  día como hoy 26 de noviembre waltford llegó, mi abuelita me decía “cuídelo como si fuera un santo”, 😎 no es  un santo, los santos si se caen se parten, él se levanta y sigue con su maravillosa sonrisa, no es un muñeco, ni supermán, es mi hijo simplemente te amo ❤️ #metoo #orangetheworld  ayer fue el día internacional de la violencia de género....todos podemos. él pudo y sólo tenía 8 añitos.... bravo 👏

their voices run through me.

text: zeitgeist films in association with kino lorber has acquired the north american rights for pamela b. green’s documentary, “be natural: the untold story of alice guy-blaché.” narrated by jodie foster, the film centers on the life and accomplishments of the world’s first female filmmaker and had its world premiere at this year’s cannes film festival. the film plays like a detective biopic in tracing the career and legacy of the pioneering guy-blaché and could not be more timely in this era of women finally beginning to get their due in the movie industry. in 1896 she wrote, directed, and produced one of the first narrative films ever made, “la fée aux choux” (the cabbage fairy). guy-blaché directed over a thousand comedies, westerns, dramas that touched on women’s empowerment, child abuse, race, immigration, and sexuality and later owned her own production company, solax, in new york. source: deadline #documentary #documentaries #doc #pioneer #filmmaker #director #producer #writer #woman #women #picoftheday #photooftheday #pictureoftheday #movie #movies #film #films #hollywood #france #history #female #instalike #career #life #first #story #metoo #legacy #instadaily

text:
"way forward for the #metoo movement"

we thank our stars to be able to bring together such great minds who will lead the conversation! our invitees will share their thoughts and opinions leading to a discussion where every attendee can share their 2 cents!

speakers - 
surabhi rao ( @_surabhirao ) - renowned fashion model who won the femina miss india 2011 (devine thoughts). she's a communication wiz and hosts personality development sessions in and around navi mumbai 
parvinder kaur - is a professor at khalsa college. also heads their emba cell and is a mentor to alot of student start-ups

mahima kukreja ( @agirlofherwords ) -  writer. poet. comic. activist. interested in intersectional feminism and its socio-political and cultural impact on youth. she's also among the initial people responsible for spearheading the #metoo movement on the indian internet

harish iyer ( @iyerharish ) - is a renowned activist for a number of causes, including promoting rights of the lgbtqia community

our host/moderator for the evening is tarun agarwal ( @india.tarun ), founder of icon business forum 
date/time - saturday, 1st dec 2018 
time - 5pm to 7pm 
address - too much drama, vashi sector 19c, palm beach road, near satra plaza. 
with another ambitious attempt to provoke a conversation, we at @toomd_in believe in the essence of this sacred movement. something that will never let it die are constant conversations on the same.

we need to get together and talk, we need to know other perspectives. we invite everyone to our first discussion in a cosy setup where anyone who attends has a voice. 
a conversation provokes change, and change is constant!

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
#pracegover: imagem de uma mulher sentada olhando para o chão com aspecto triste ou de preocupação. na parede, ao lado dela, o seguinte dizer: "os crimes de lesão corporal praticados contra a mulher no âmbito doméstico e familiar são de ação penal pública incondicionada. are 773765 - tema 0713"

a tese de repercussão geral de hoje também se relaciona com esse momento de conscientização social em prol da redução dos alarmantes números de violência doméstica contra a mulher. 
mas o que isso significa na prática?

havendo provas suficientes para o ingresso da ação penal, o ministério público deve processar o agressor, mesmo que a vítima se manifeste contrariamente a isso. ou seja, a vontade da vítima não é uma condição para que seu agressor seja processado. 
o representante do ministério público do paraná, neste caso, manifestou que "condicionar o exercício da ação penal à representação da ofendida extremamente fragilizada pela reiterada violência sofrida e emocionalmente comprometida pelas relações de afeto até então existentes implica manter, por ausência de resposta penal adequada, o quadro de impunidade dos agressores." e você o que pensa sobre isso?

text:
jean-paul gauthier a abandonné la fourrure des animaux dans ses collections

le célèbre créateur de mode français jean-paul gauthier n'utilisera plus la fourrure dans ses collections.

sur l'arrêt de l'utilisation de la fourrure gauthier a annoncé la chaîne de télévision en direct canal+. le créateur de mode a admis que malgré le fait qu'il a utilisé la fourrure dès le début de sa carrière, il a décidé d'abandonner cette tradition. la raison en était le côté éthique de la question-le sadisme sur les animaux. "vous pouvez trouver la fausse fourrure ou d'autres façons de garder au chaud. peut-être que cela aidera à faire preuve d'une plus grande créativité qui ne nuit à personne... parce que la façon dont les animaux sont tués est sans aucun doute terrible", a souligné le concepteur.

l'utilisation de la fourrure animale au cours des dernières années a également refusé de nombreuses marques de mode, y compris burberry, armani, hugo boss, ralph lauren, tommy hilfiger, michael kors, versace, gucci, giorgio armani, john galliano et d'autres.

rappelons, à la semaine de la mode de londres pour la première fois, il n'y avait pas de fourrure. bien que les organisateurs n'aient pas officiellement interdit l'utilisation de la fourrure, aucun des concepteurs participant à l'événement n'a commencé à utiliser ce matériel dans ses collections #moda #paris #parisienne #paris16eme #jardinduluxemburg #jacadi #petitbateau  #photo #nice #marseille #lion #menton #toulouse #chaton #chat #chien #nicolashulot #macron #emanuelmacron #metoo❤️ #metoo #femme #voiture #france🇫🇷

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
"si la vie était une pomme, croque la à pleines dents" (de guayguay)
🌿
🌿
hier était une journée spéciale pour moi: c'était la journée contre la violence faite aux femmes.
🌿
🌿
les violences faites aux femmes peuvent être exercées dans tous les domaines de vie et sous toutes les formes (physiques, psychologiques, verbales..).
🌿
🌿
1 femmes sur 3 est toujours victime de violence physique ou sexuelle.. je trouve ça inadmissible. mais le plus dur, c'est de ne pas être écouté. quand la personne se comporte différemment avec votre famille, vos amis... personne ne vous croit. on vous dit que vous exagérer tout. et ce sentiment de solitude s'installe et vous pensez devoir vivre seule face à vos démons. or personne ne sait ce qu'il se passe une fois que la porte de votre maison est fermée.
🌿
🌿
pour toutes ces femmes qui ont ce sentiment, comme j'ai pu l'avoir... sachez que vous n'êtes pas seule !! on est jamais totalement seule.. on aura toujours une épaule sur laquelle pleurer, une main tendue qu'on doit attraper et une personne pour nous sauver. alors soyez forte et battez vous !
-
-
-

text:
após a grande onda provocada pelo movimento #metoo, foi a vez da frança se manifestar contra a violência de gênero, no último sábado (24), as ruas foram o palco de mulheres e apoiadores da pauta. 
as reivindicações contaram com a questão da violência, demonstrando um quadro complicada para as mulheres, considerando que diariamente mais de 250 mulheres são violentadas por companheiros ou ex companheiros. 
além disso, abordou a questão da ciberviolência de gênero, muitas das mulheres que denunciaram abusos e violências sofridas tem se sentido ameaçadas e perseguidas por homens nas redes, uma violência que invade a privacidade delas, altera senhas e as coagem em troca de silêncio pelos atos violentos cometidos. 
as francesas deixaram um recado claro para o mundo, a vida das mulheres importa e precisa ser discutida de forma ampla e responsável, implantando políticas públicas capazes de reverter esse cenário violento e opressor.

https://www.em.com.br/app/noticia/internacional/2018/11/24/interna_internacional,1007885/varias-marchas-feministas-na-europa-contra-a-violencia-de-genero.shtml
.
.
.

text: preity zinta on her comment on metoo: it’s ironic that someone who went through abuse has to clarify actor preity zinta’s comments on metoo movement in a recent interview earned her a lot of backlash for shaming victims and laughing about sexual harassment. she has now released a statement on twitter, in which, she has said that her comments were taken out of context. “to all the women out there. i am sorry if i have unintentionally hurt your sentiments on the #metoo movement. it’s ironic that someone who has gone through abuse, as i have, has to clarify this,” she wrote in her statement. preity was asked in an interview if she has experience harassment. she said she ‘wished’ something like this would have happened to her just so she could respond to the journalist’s comments. her words drew the ire of twitter for belittling the trauma of sexual harassment victims. preity gave clarifications for her words in a series of tweets: “my reason for saying ‘i wish something like this would have happened to me’ in the film industry with a smile was because i would have reacted and slapped the person. so it never happened and much later when it happened i did react and the whole world saw it.”

text_retweet:
[sempatkan menonton‼️]
kita harus ada untuk menemani dan mendengarkan para survivor ketika mereka mulai mengumpulkan keberanian untuk bercerita. kita juga harus ikut berjuang untuk orang-orang yang tidak bisa berjuang untuk dirinya sendiri. something has to be done to make a change and the power of change is in our hand.

hari ini adalah hari kedua 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign.
ini adalah waktu kita untuk beraksi mengakhiri kekerasan terhadap perempuan, baik anak, remaja, maupun dewasa di seluruh dunia dan un women dengan 25 influencer indonesian membuat video pendek sebagai bagian dari kampanye to end violence against women.

kampanye tahun ini bertemakan orange the world: #hearmetoo karena suara para survivor dan aktivis melalui kampanye #metoo, #timesup, dan sebagainya telah mencapai puncaknya pada beberapa tahun terakhir ini. meskipun nama dan konteksnya mungkin berbeda di seluruh lokasi, tapi kekerasan tetaplah kekerasan, pelecehan tetaplah pelecehan and their story need to be brought to light.

let yourself be heard💕✨ #hearmetoo
#orangetheworld #16daysofactivism #lawankekerasan #16haktp
#repost from #yollavends

kita harus ada untuk menemani dan mendengarkan para survivor ketika mereka mulai mengumpulkan keberanian untuk bercerita. kita juga harus ikut berjuang untuk orang-orang yang tidak bisa berjuang untuk dirinya sendiri. something has to be done to make a change and the power of change is in our hand.

hari ini adalah hari kedua 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign.
ini adalah waktu kita untuk beraksi mengakhiri kekerasan terhadap perempuan, baik anak, remaja, maupun dewasa di seluruh dunia dan un women dengan 25 influencer indonesian membuat video pendek sebagai bagian dari kampanye to end violence against women.

kampanye tahun ini bertemakan orange the world: #hearmetoo karena suara para survivor dan aktivis melalui kampanye #metoo, #timesup, dan sebagainya telah mencapai puncaknya pada beberapa tahun terakhir ini. meskipun nama dan konteksnya mungkin berbeda di seluruh lokasi, tapi kekerasan tetaplah kekerasan, pelecehan tetaplah pelecehan and their story need to be brought to light.

let yourself be heard💕✨ #hearmetoo

text:
dr fiona vera-grey (bottom left) is an academic at durham university and an expert in sexual violence against women prevention. she has worked in services including rape crisis, and research for 10 - 15 years, it’s safe to say - she is an incredible woman and she knows her shit! we were blessed to such a knowledgable woman write the foreword to our book. 📖
she was one of the panelists at our event ‘the art of consent’, this is just some of what she had to say - "we need to provide spaces for women and young women to be together and to talk about the way that we’ve been affected by gender socialisation, we’re taught to take up less space, to reduce ourselves, to doubt ourselves - that really came out of the documentary film, the way were taught to doubt our own experience of something. we know what it is, but we’re taught to doubt what it is.

art - poetry, film, songs - can connect emotionally, develop empathy, around sexual violence in particular, what we need is for people to connect emotionally because it’s a hard subject. we want to be defended, we want to be removed from it, we want to find excuses. but it’s important for us to connect and feel together.”
👏
📸 by @gorrangorra ✨ more photos from the event on the website! (link in bio) and a lil video is coming soon!

text:
today’s podcast episode tackles pay parity in surfing! pay inequality exists across all industries — especially in sports. the world surf league recently announced that it will award equal prize money to male and female athletes beginning 2019. 
because of this, the world surf league will become the first and only us based global sports league (and among the first internationally) to achieve prize money equality. 
on this week’s episode, i speak with sophie goldschmidt, the league’s first female ceo, who will share why the league is taking this momentous step and what this means for female athletes across the world. link in bio to listen👆

text:
one of my favorite platforms for mental health topics the mighty had recently published an article on a connection between mental health& allergies and asthma (original research was published in front psychiatry magazine). "the increased risk of developing a mental illness if you have allergies or asthma is likely because of inflammation. [...] about one-third of patients with depression - the same percentage who don't respond to antiderpessant medications - have a high level of immune system activation that may be the cause of their depression.".
living with a chronic illness is stressful, like walking on a thin ice - you never know what it will break out and take you down. i wish doctors to start taking that into consideration soon when treating patients who suffer from depression, anxiety, eating disorder and other mental illnesses.

text:
ב"צירוף מקרים" שרק הקב"ה לבדו יכול היה לרקום, בשבת קראנו בתורה את פרשת "וישלח", על העינוי הנורא שעוברת דינה, בתם של יעקב ולאה ובדיוק השבוע, העולם מציין את יום המאבק באלימות נגד נשים.

יותר ויותר מסתבר, שזה הנושא הבוער של הזמן הזה.
פתאום ערכים של קדושה, טהרה וכבוד כלפי נשים,
מקבלים כותרות ראשיות ולא יורדים מסדר היום במשך חודשים ארוכים. פתאום שאלות כמו "למה עד עכשיו לא התלוננת"
זוכות לשיתוף ולהקשבה. ואנחנו מגלים, שכמעט ואֵין בַּיִת אֲשֶׁר אֵין שָׁם מֵת.

לנושא הזה בדיוק הקדישה הרבנית ימימה את השיעור האחרון.
לאחר שענתה למאות שאלות בנושא הזה, במייל ופנים אל פנים,
לאחר שהתלוותה לא פעם לבנות למתן עדות במשטרה ולעימותים מול תוקפים, וכעת היא כותבת בפרשנות רחבת 
יריעה, עבור העיניים שמבקשות מענה. מנויות פרשה ואשה קיבלו את השיעור הזה לפני שבת, ואני מזמינה גם אותך למצוא בו תשובות לשאלות הבוערות. ✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨
זה מה שתמצאי בקובץ, בין היתר - • הסיבה האמיתית לכך שלא התלוננת ולמה כדאי להתלונן
• חמש תגובות אפשריות כלפי תוקפנות. והמלצת הרבנית
• איך לעבוד נכון עם הפחד
• הבדלה בין הרוע לבינך - איך עושים את זה
• מי ינקום את נקמתך? וקריאה למורים ולמחנכים
• איפה היו אבא ואמא כשזה קרה
• וכשהנפש תתרפא, הגוף, מה יהיה איתו
• נוסחה אלטרנטיבית לשמירה על הילדים
(את זה לא יאמרו לך בשום מרכז לנפגעות)
• ודמעות-הזהב שלך, לאן הן הולכות
• מילה לאמא / לאשה של תוקף
✨✨✨
וכמיטב המסורת הימימית,
והכל יוצא מתוך פרשת השבוע
ולא מפספס את הקשר ההדוק לחג המתקרב - חנוכה,
שהוא חג האור של המוטרדות, המותקפות והנפגעות.

שיעור שהוא בשורה. אוויר לנשימה.
הוא בא לגלות את יופייך, את אורך
ולתת בידייך כלים אישיים למאבק ברוע.

מיד לאחר ביצוע התשלום, השיעור יישלח אליך ישירות למייל שלך. ***את הקישור לטופס התשלום הפשוט והמאובטח תמצאי בתגובה הראשונה.** *

בשורות טובות-טובות,
יקרת
✨✨✨

#פרשהואשה 
#הרבניתימימהמזרחי

stop_filter_tweet: ב '' צירוף מקרים '' שרק הקב '' ה לבדו יכול היה לרקום , בשבת קראנו בתורה את פרשת `` וישלח '' , על העינוי הנורא שעוברת דינה , בתם של יעקב ולאה ובדיוק השבוע , העולם מציין את יום המאבק באלימות נגד נשים . יותר ויותר מסתבר , שזה הנושא הבוער של הזמן הזה . פתאום ערכים של קדושה , טהרה וכבוד כלפי נשים , מקבלים כותרות ראשיות ולא יורדים מסדר היום במשך חודשים ארוכים . פתאום שאלות כמו `` למה עד עכשיו לא התלוננת '' זוכות לשיתוף ולהקשבה . ואנחנו מגלים , שכמעט ואֵין בַּיִת אֲשֶׁר אֵין שָׁם מֵת . לנושא הזה בדיוק הקדישה הרבנית ימימה את השיעור האחרון . לאחר שענתה למאות שאלות בנושא הזה , במייל ופנים אל פנים , לאחר שהתלוותה לא פעם לבנות למתן עדות במשטרה ולעימותים מול תוקפים , וכעת היא כותבת בפרשנות רחבת יריעה , עבור העיניים שמבקשות מענה . מנויות פרשה ואשה קיבלו את השיעור הזה לפני שבת , ואני מזמינה גם אותך למצוא בו תשובות לשאלות הבוערות . ✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨ זה מה שתמצאי בקובץ , בין היתר - • הסיבה האמיתית לכך שלא התלוננת ולמה כדאי להתלונן • חמש תגובות אפשריות כלפי תוקפנות . והמלצת הרבנית • איך לעבוד נכון עם הפחד • הבדלה בין הרוע לבינך - איך עושים את זה • מי ינקום את נקמתך ? וקריאה למורים ולמחנכים • איפה היו אבא ואמא כשזה קרה • וכשהנפש תתרפא , הגוף , מה יהיה איתו • נוסחה אלטרנטיבית לשמירה על הילדים ( את זה לא יאמרו לך בשום מרכז לנפגעות ) • ודמעות-הזהב שלך , לאן הן הולכות • מילה לאמא / לאשה של תוקף ✨✨✨ וכמיטב המסורת הימימית , והכל יוצא מתוך פרשת השבוע ולא מפספס את הקשר ההדוק לחג המתקרב - חנוכה , שהוא חג האור של המוטרדות , המותקפות והנפגעות . שיעור שהוא בשורה . אוויר לנשימה . הוא בא לגלות את יופייך , את אורך ולתת בידייך כלים אישיים למאבק ברוע . מיד לאחר ביצוע התשלום , השיעור יישלח אליך ישירות למייל שלך . ***את הקישור לטופס התשלום הפשוט והמאובטח תמצאי בתגובה הראשונה . ** * בשורות טובות-טובות , יקרת ✨✨✨

text:
on this international day to ending violence against women and girls, intersectional feminist foreign policy are launching their 1st edition of their uninvited women journal, providing a platform for the voices of women who are never seen or heard and certainly not invited to sit around the table on issues that impact their lives. 
when me and shaista aziz set this up last year, we were overwhelmed by the interest and the massive need to have different voices, with real experience, and real issues represented and a different form of leadership. 
a massive thank you to our volunteers nuran y ra and chloe roesch who’ve worked hard putting it all together. and our contributors and the many more women who expressed interest. #endviolenceagainstwomen #hearmetoo #metoo #aidtoo #feminism 
check it out and share 🤲🏻 https://www.intersectionalffp.org/first-edition

text:
[rol de las madres ante la violencia contra la mujer] "la violencia contra mujeres y niñas es una de las violaciones de los derechos humanos más extendidas, persistentes y devastadoras del mundo actual sobre las que apenas se informa debido a la impunidad de la cual disfrutan los perpetradores, y el silencio, la estigmatización y la vergüenza que sufren las víctimas." (un.org)
. ¿qué podemos hacer como madres y desde nuestros hogares para luchar la violencia contra la mujer y eliminarla?
pienso que podemos:
🔶respetar a las mujeres de la familia y no discriminarlas, ni estigmatizarlas, ni avergonzarlas por su género.
🔶dejar de criar machos y princesas para criar seres humanos de bien. 🔶creer en nuestras hijas antes que dudar de sus historias.
🔶enseñar a nuestros hij@s a respetar a todas las personas como individuos válidos y capaces independientemente del género.
🔶conectar emocionalmente con nuestras hijas para escucharlas mejor. incluso a sus silencios.
🔶enseñar a nuestros hij@s a reconocer la violencia y denunciarla. 
se me ocurren muchas más, pero quisiera saber que piensan ustedes.

i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
every  year from 25 november (the international day for the elimination of violence against women) to 10 december (human rights day) the 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign is a time to inspire action to end violence against women and girls around the world.  the campaign was launched in 2008 by un secretary-general ban ki-moon. recently, through campaigns such as #metoo and #timesup, voices of survivors and activists have shown that women and girls everywhere are experiencing extensive abuse and their stories need to be brought to light. therefore the global advocacy theme of this years campain is: orange the world: #hearmetoo

text: victim blaming attitudes really trigger me. when i was in a violent relationship, a friend said that it’s my fault for putting myself through such hardship. i had a choice, why didn’t i leave? oh god it still triggers me. and it’s so common to have this response, from society in general but often from friends, family and people we trust.  let me put one thing straight - all abuse happens because the perpetrator decides to abuse. that’s it. every speculation about what could have been done to prevent it is irrelevant, useless and traumatises the victim further. victim blaming can come from a person looking for security “if it’s the person’s fault then it can’t happen to me, i can prevent it”. or it can come from arrogance and a false sense of superiority “i’m special this sort of thing only happens to the weak minded”. but abuse can happen for a wide range of reasons and the only common denominator is the person who decides to abuse. all the people out there who further traumatise abuse victims with your sickening victim blaming and inappropriate blame and questioning - just stop. you’re being awful human beings. educate yourself, make sure you talk to another human being from the perspective of empathy and kindness. stop being the reason why survivors are afraid to speak up. your attitude sustains the culture in which survivors have to stay in the shadow and bear the burden of their trauma. they really should not have to. fellow survivors - don’t ever listen to the ignorant voices of victim blaming. it’s not your fault. it’s not your fault. it’s never, ever, ever your fault. #bpd #borderline #mentalhealth #victimblaming #metoo #borderlinepersonalitydisorder #mentalhealthawareness #recovery #domesticviolence #emotionalabuse #abuse #abusesurvivor #recovery #recoveryispossible #recoverywin #abusedwomen #abuseawareness #narcissisticabuse #stopchildabuse #abusesurvivors

text_retweet:
repost from @belinda_vegan ・・・
▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️swipe 👈
_
it doesn't have to be this way!
we all make choices throughout the day that have enormous impact on others whether we realize it or not. every time we chose what to eat, buy, and wear, our decision can support unfathomable violence and brutality towards animals.
_
if you can live your life without harming others, why wouldn't you?
_
all animal agriculture, from backyard operations to factory farms, is based on inflicting great physical and psychological pain on its victims before subjecting them to a violent, untimely death. mutilations like debeaking, detoeing, dehorning, tooth scraping, tail docking, nose ringing, branding and castration (all done without anesthesia) are routine in all “free range” farming. so is confinement (albeit to larger cages). so is the denial of a natural life. and, of course, regardless how farmed animals live their short, captive lives, they all end up being slaughtered. have you seen what happens in a slaughterhouses? you can rest assured, that there is nothing humane that occurs there. it's the stuff of nightmares.

if living ethically is important to you, please remember that there is nothing humane about “humane” animal farming, just as there is nothing ethical or defensible about consuming its "products." when confronted with the fundamental injustice inherent in all animal agriculture—a system that is predicated on inflicting massive, intentional and unnecessary suffering and death on billions of sentient individuals—the only ethical response is to strive to end it by becoming vegan.

all animal agriculture, from backyard operations to factory farms, is based on inflicting great physical and psychological pain on its victims before subjecting them to a violent, untimely death. mutilations like debeaking, detoeing, dehorning, tooth scraping, tail docking, nose ringing, branding and castration (all done without anesthesia) are routine in all “free range” farming. so is confinement (albeit to larger cages). so is the denial of a natural life. and, of course, regardless how farmed animals live their short, captive lives, they all end up being slaughtered. have you seen what happens in a slaughterhouses? you can rest assured, that there is nothing humane that occurs there. it is the stuff of nightmares.

if living ethically is important to you, please remember that there is nothing humane about “humane” animal farming, just as there is nothing ethical or defensible about consuming its "products." when confronted with the fundamental injustice inherent in all animal agriculture—a system that is predicated on inflicting massive, intentional and unnecessary suffering and death on billions of sentient individuals—the only ethical response is to strive to end it by becoming vegan.

#belinda_vegan

text:
ciclo de la violencia ❗️⚠️👇🏼 1.fase de acumulación de tensión: esta etapa puede tener una duración indeterminada, desde días, semanas, meses o años. ocurren incidentes menores como gritos o pequeñas peleas. se acumula la tensión y aumenta la violencia verbal.

2.  fase de explosión: se producen de forma ya visible los malos tratos, tanto psicológicos, como físicos y/o sexuales (o cualquiera de los tipos de violencia). ya en esta fase se producen estados de ansiedad y temor en la persona receptora de violencia, que suelen conducirla a  pedir ayuda o a tomar la decisión de denunciar al generador de violencia.

3. luna de miel:  es la fase del arrepentimiento y la reconciliación. tras los episodios violentos, el generador de violencia suele pedir perdón, mostrarse amable y cariñoso y arrepentido. el generador puede llegar a hacer creer a la víctima que la violencia se ha producido como consecuencia de una actitud de ella, que ella la ha provocado, haciendo incluso que esta llegue a creerlo. 
comparte para hacer consciencia.

text:
tres, dos, uno…el despertador sonó presto sin ningún atisbo de piedad en su estrepitoso concierto. quería seguir durmiendo un poco más, sin embargo, la incansable rutina de mi trabajo vaticinaba la onerosa causa, a la vez que consecuencia, de la elección de mi medio de vida: salario abusivo, jefe distraído, falta de seguridad laboral…factores que apuntan describiendo por sí mismos, a la precaria situación económica que el país enfrentaba. me puse en pie e intenté levantarme de la cama con un vago movimiento. encendí la radio sin prestar demasiada atención al programa matutino de música de la cadena predeterminada ya en el aparato, y enseguida comenzó a retransmitirse la canción “oh my love” de elvis persley. era una dedicatoria de una mujer a su marido por sus bodas de oro. pensé que era una ñoñería y que poco podría atraerme la idea de compartir la mayor parte de mi tiempo con una persona de la cual ignorar absolutamente todo lo que no acabara de convencerme o directamente me hiciera daño, solo por miedo a la repercusión y a las consecuencias que podría tener en mi propia vida. clara era mi falta de tendencia a basar mi pensamiento en la antigua concepción del matrimonio. fui a la cocina a prepararme un desayuno con gran carga calórica ya que me sentía bastante débil y me decanté por unos sabrosos huevos con bacon y un zumo de naranja. en la estación, todos los trabajadores estábamos esperando impacientes al tren que nos trasladaría a nuestros respectivos puestos para supuestamente colaborar con el avance de la sociedad, aunque la realidad subyacente fuera mucho más fría y cruda que los motivos que justificaban el resultado del esfuerzo conjunto de toda esta gente: la supervivencia. el traqueteo se podía diferenciar cerca y las vías comenzaron a temblar anunciando su llegada. nos apelotonamos en los vagones cual hormiguero y el vehículo arrancó.

text:
for english scroll down-- بعد إذني "عيب ما تقوليش لأ، اقعدي علي حجر عمو واديله بوسة"
"مش فاكرة إنى قولتله آه، ولا إني قلتله لأ، مش فاكرة إنه سأل أصلا"
"تلاقيكي بـيـنـتي له إنك عايزة، ما هو هـ يسأل ليه إلا لو كان شاف واحدة شكلها عايزة"

كتير بـ يحصلنا مواقف من غير موافقتنا في علاقتنا بالآخرين، من أول طريقة سلام مش حابينها حتى لو من حد قريب، لحد الموافقة المفترضة في العلاقات الزوجية

في إطار حملة الـ 16 يوم لمناهضة العنف ضد المرأة، تقوم خريطة التحرش ومشروع بصى بحملة مشتركة عن الموافقة في العلاقات وأهميتها في تحديد الأفعال التي تعتبر تحرش أو عنف جنسي
 تقوم بصى خلال شهر نوفمبر وديسمبر بنشر قصص من سيدات ورجال عن تجارب تعرضوا لها في علاقاتهم الشخصية مع آخرين بدون موافقتهم

لمشاركة القصص برجاء ملء الاستمارة: https://goo.gl/forms/daazuqogqqgarexg3

لمتابعة الحملة علي @harassmap  #بعد_إذني #بصى #خريطة_التحرش #16_يوم #التحرش_في_الشارع

ask first “it’s impolite to say no. go sit on your uncle’s lap and give him a kiss!”
“i don’t remember saying yes. i don’t remember saying no. i don’t remember being asked at all”
“you probably implied that you wanted it. why would he even ask you when you look like someone who’d want it?’ from an unwanted handshake or hug—even from the people closest to us—to the so-called “implied consent” in marital sexual intercourse, we’re often put in situations that happen without our consent 
the bussy project and harassmap are launching a joint campaign within the framework of the “16 days of activism to end violence against women” campaign about consent in relationships and its importance in defining what constitutes sexual harassment and sexual violence

to share your story please use our anonymous form: https://goo.gl/forms/daazuqogqqgarexg3

to follow the campaign, please check out @harassmap

#askfirst #bussy #harassmap #gendertech #16days #metoo #storytelling #endsh #orangetheworld

text:
*women rights*

human rights are women rights and women rights are human rights. let's end violence against women and girls! 
_
25 november is the international day to end violence against women. unfortunately, women do still have to fight for their rights and security every day, everywhere on this planet. we need effective political decisions and actions to end this!
_
saturday 24 november was a great day in france. tens of thousands of people were united in the streets to protest violence against women. demonstrations drew around 50000 according to organizer #noustoutes. it was a fantastic feminist tidal wave against gender violence. we are waiting for powerful political actions now. 
_
there were also many other womens' protests in europe, like in rome, geneva, athens or madrid. let's be united in europe and the world! #sorority #sororité

you can join nous toutes movement here: @noustoutes2411 + noustoutes.org
_
and let's join the un #16days of activism against gender-based violence campaign, because it is really time to end all kinds of violence against women and girls everywhere in the world! #orangetheworld 
the campaign starts today, the international day for the elimination of violence against women, and ends 10 december, human rights day. @unwomen
more information:
http://www.unwomen.org/en/what-we-do/ending-violence-against-women/take-action/16-days-of-activism
#hearmetoo
_
#genderequality #education #solidarity #timesup #stopviolencesfaitesauxfemmes #droitsdesfemmes #metoo #lifestyle #stopviolence #humanrights #womenrights  #stopviolenceagainstwomen #womenempowerment #feminisme #sisterhood #girlpower #riseup #sexism #feminism #violencesfaitesauxfemmes #violenceagainstwomen #stoprape #sexisme #endvaw
name: Mirka Maarit : My Wonder World

text:
understanding rape culture 101

in a recent poll by thomas reuters foundation, india was ranked as the least safe country in the world for women, discerned as having the worst record of rapes, sexual harassment and violence against women.

this poll might be hard to believe for many indians, but the truth is that we live in a culture that normalises rape, violence and harassment against women. rape culture refers to the tendency of seeing violence and misogyny as an expression or part of ‘tradition’ or ‘culture’ and begins with our everyday use of sexist language and glorification of sexual violence in popular culture.

degradation of women, evident through numerous incidents such as eve-teasing (street sexual harassment), groping, flashing, revenge porn, stalking, among others, is a consequence of day-to-day normalised sexist behaviour. they are a result of certain actions and beliefs that normalise rape.

violence against women does not take place in isolation; it is a part of systematic rape culture. it starts with normalisation of rape and sexual assaults, leading to degradation of women, which finally perpetuates into more violent and sexual assaults. actions and attitudes we term as ‘harmless’ and ‘not related to rape’ are in fact part of this structure and reinforce, as well as excuse, more violent sexual acts.
.
.

text:
roma ,25 novembre .
assemblea nazionale non una di meno.
“a tutte voi è stato detto di non parlare e che probabilmente ve lo meritavate.forse dovevate anche ringraziare delle offese che stavate ricevendo.
spesso abbiamo vittime di violenza accanto e nemmeno lo sappiamo,anzi fino a quando non ci si capita ci si domanda come si fa a non saper reagire o scappare.peccato che finché non si è dentro non si capiscono molte cose.
le parole feriscono come le mani.a volte distruggono .
mi sono sentita in errore e che lo ero anche io mi è stato detto a chiare parole e certo che mi hanno dato della pazza e ma si avevo capito male,facendomi sentire colpevole dello stato in cui ero.
cosa è una minaccia?solo quella di morte o di botte o basta fare del male a qualcuno facendogli credere come è successo a me “che quelli come me fanno una brutta fine e anche se racconti le cose io negherò tutto fino alla morte”.
tutti vi diranno è normale o al massimo un mi dispiace e se va bene vi vergognerete pure perché si pensa che ci si merita quel trattamento.
e invece non è così.non è normale.
la cosa che fa più male è ripercorrere ogni volta i ricordi e non riuscire a crederci o trovare una spiegazione razionale a quelle parole,offese,situazioni che avete vissuto.
vi avranno detto di stare in silenzio invece non va bene,perché siete state vittime di violenza e la violenza non ha mai giustificazione.
come si ricomincia?non lo so forse dicendo la verità non tanto per se stesse ma perché è dovere morale di noi in quanto persone.
ogni mattina ci si pensa.
ma nonostante tutto si può rialzare voce e testa”. #nonunadimeno #roma #25novembre #nomore #stopviolence #metoo #movement #nonènormalechesianormale

text_retweet:
repost @the_art_tiffin .
chains and boundaries. [trigger warning] ▪️
today is international day of elimination of violence against women, and it is harrowing to read the statistics. at least  100 uk women killed by men or where a man is the principal suspect by 24 september this year 100 women in 267 days is one woman dead every 2.6 days.  over 20% of women in england and wales have suffered some form of sexual violence since the age of 16. considering rape or attempted rape alone it is 5.5% and 0.3%. these are shocking statistics, and yet we hear more in uk media about immigration and about terrorism.
.
▪️
so many women do not come forwards. so many women come forwards but are not believed. and so many women are made to feel ashamed by questions such as ‘so why did you stay?’ dv and abuse takes different forms and coercive control is one of them, which is not so easy to prove and not easy to escape from. abuse of any form breaks down the spirit and self-worth and self-esteem something which prevents so many women leaving until it is too late. we need to have more stringent legal systems in place, and we have to believe women. let us end of culture of silence and let us put survivors at the centre of any action @unwomen we have to enable more women to share their stories without shame and stigma, and we have to consider the multi-faceted nature of abuse and violence. and for any man who says ‘what about men’, honestly do have a considered look at your unconscious biases, and instead think of what you can do to help this. ▪️ .
#unwomen #hearmenow #orangetheworld #believethesurvivors #metoo #timeisup #womenempowerment #womenempoweringwomen #internationaldayofeliminationofviolenceagainstwomen #limitlessboundaries #tedxwomen #tedxfpwomen #tedxformbypointwomen #liverpool #liverpoolgirls #femchats #womeninhistory #empoweringwomen #feminist #feministaf #womenempoweringwomen #thefeministway #smashthepatriarchy #femaleempowerment #standupspeakup

text:
after this woman survived a homophobic and misogynist attack, her assailants were let free while she was arrested. alongside ni una menos, she is advocating for her record to be wiped and for justice to be done. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for “femicide,” the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio. 
#opensociety #argentina #niunamenos #femicide #femicidio #conmisderechosnotemetas #16days #genderbasedviolence #metoo #hearmetoo #homophobia

text:
kikelomo woleosho's boy project.
 i have spent 85% of my advocacy talking to girls and women. now my team and i have decided to take boys more seriously. we want to influence and positively affect our boys and men.

i have a 14 yr old brother and i want him to view life and women from a beautiful perspective. beyond my brother, i want to reach out to his male friends, his male neighbors and other boys in our community, nigeria and africa.

our first boy project is going to be a lunch meeting for boys in the underserved community of agbado. 
it will be a 2hours 30mins meeting with a distinguished man who is living purpose and is willing to impact the next male generation.

we hope this experience serves as a memorial for the boys to aim at achieving the future that will change africa.

like i always say together we can change our community a person at a time.

#boysproject #boys #boysempowerment
#kikelomowoleosho #kikelomoboaz #boysprojectbykikelomo #communitydevelopment #mentoring #hearmetoo #metoo #notoviolence #chnageinafrica #africa #mondaymotivation

thanks to aisling from #dorset for this beautiful portrait of gaia, calling for justice for her. #artforgaia a project that hopes to bring together contributions from artists, the public and survivors, in memory of gaia pope & to highlight injustice around sexual violence, mental health and inequality. 
gaia was an artist and a survivor of sexual violence who struggled with #ptsd in the lead up to her disappearance and death in november 2018 when she was just 19 years old. what happened to gaia has become a national story and her family, who lead the @justiceforgaia campaign, want to use this platform to highlight the challenges faced by her and so many others. 
the art for gaia project, which is being followed by bbc news, is one way the campaign seeks to raise awareness and create a space where people can be heard, the way gaia deserved to be heard. 
to find out more, click the website link on our profile.
